status_message: b'Ye kahan milega?? Any leads.......'
b'What good to eat near nursery area.. I guess I heard about Bun Kebab A lot...'
b'Where I can dine pizza in this time towards Clifton area?'

b'Met this Kid Junaid near Donisl 5 star Food Street opposite Chopsoy. GOOGLE Fries, one of the tastiest and crispy fries I have had. Offering some unique flavors. Kid wears gloves and uses plastic plates, He even explained why these plates are more hygienic than the plates used by chatwalas and other french fries stalls.

Has a facebook page @googlefrenchfries

I urge to people living close by to visit his stall and encourage him so he keeps his dream of launching zinger burgers'

b'So finally me and my friend went to "bite 4 delight". It was crowded and I had to wait for approximately 15 minutes to receive my order. 
Majority of the people on waiting line were having their first purchase from here (I asked about their reviews and they had no idea how this pizza like substance tastes like). So finally I got my order and took a seat with my friend to taste it for the first time.
Man it was not that good. It was seriously a waste of money and time as I had to travel 36km to reach this stall at dhoraji. 
Explaining my experience in simple words:
1st layer of cheese was good but once you finish this layer, all you get is potato fries dipped in mayo and some sauce (no cheese in the 2nd layer of fries).
Totally over rated.
Total damage Rs. 320 for 2 cheese pizza fries.'

b'The best chargah in all over karachi... Boht sab try kiaa but is jaisa CHARGAH na kahin hai na miley ga..#ghosia #silverspoon.. Near Hussainabad food street.. Every buddy must try.... I luv it from last 10 years...'

b"So today I visited there first time and loved it, it's way too better than Chai Wala and other Chai spots, beautiful ambiance and separate decent place for families. \nApart from this, good taste doodh pati \xf0\x9f\x91\x8c and they serve food too."

b"Had dinner at Chef Zakir's Restaurant C Z (Gulshan) overall it was'nt a good experience.Food was good in taste but too less in quantity. 

We paid Rs 7500/- for this :/ 

Ambiance : 9/10
Service : 10/10
Food Quality : 10/10
Taste : 7/10
Quantity : 1/10
Value of Money : 2/10 

Ps : The BBQ Platter u can see in picture cost Rs 2500/-"

b"I call this one The Exam Acer!
If you've got a night full of cramming ahead, and your head decides to stop cooperating (you have a headache) and sleep's about to take over, you make this:

\xe2\x80\xa2 2 teaspoons coffee
\xe2\x80\xa2 2 tablespoons chocolate powder
\xe2\x80\xa2 1 tablespoon Nutella (heaped)
\xe2\x80\xa2 sugar (to taste)
\xe2\x80\xa2 1 cup milk
\xe2\x80\xa2 2 tablespoons cream
\xe2\x80\xa2 1 sachet Qarshi Johar Joshanda

Whip together Nutella, sugar, cream, coffee, Qarshi Johar Joshanda and chocolate powder until a smooth paste forms. Pour over boiling hot milk. Stir. Sip. 
Let the drink do its work (give it 10 minutes) and get back to your books. The Joshanda does wonders for the head and the caffeine gives you the boost you need to ace that exam!
Good luck!

#SehatKaFlavour #SehatKaFlavor #Qarshi #JoharJoshanda"

So after many posts about pizza fries at khadda market (Big Bash) I finally decided to check out if the hype was worth it or not. 

I ordered pizza fries, chipotle fries, beef lasagne, creamy tikka pizza and buffalo chicken pizza.

The pizza fries, were pretty good even though I was disappointed to discover they didn't have marinara sauce in them. Over all they were creamy, fresh and all the ingredients went well together. Were they exceptional? No. Would I go again to eat them? Yes   
rating: 4/5

The chipotle fries were good but not better then the pizza fries in my Opinion, though I did love the chipotle sauce on them.
3.4/5

The pizza's were average, nothing that stood out among other pizza's I have tried. The mustard sauce on buffalo chicken pizza didn't go well with the other flavours in it, it simply didn't work for me. 2.5-3ish/5

We had mixed reviews on the beef lasagne. My friend hated it while I liked it alot. It had a mild flavour ( again I think it would have been alot better with marinara). For me it was 3.5/5

On to the service. Very disappointing. The restaurant was a small place, even though full it was nothing 3-4 waiter's couldn't handle but still the service was extremely slow. The waiter's either did their best to make sure no eye contact was made with the customers or simply looked away when called. When they finally came, each time whatever I asked for was either forgotten ( had to ask someone else about it again till I got it) or just took way too long. The food service being slow is something excusable but why did it take so long to bring the drinks after serving the food? And more still to bring a bottle of water ( all this the waiter was standing 2 feet away, idle) which was ordered with the food. 
Being a foodie, maybe I am just used to 5 star service and the bar is set too high.
 
Would I go again? Probably not, bad service really ruins the experience, especially since so many other options are Available with equally good food and much much faster service. If the service gets improved, the place is decent."

b'-

So, I finally got to try the new innovation---Sheriff Kuntucky Burger. And this time KFC pretty much lived up to its slogan; "Finger licking good".

The main ingredients of the burger are Zinger fillet and pepperoni. A combination, I hadn't tried before this. In addition to that, there is cheese, lettuce,   bbq sauce and caramelized onions with heavy amount of black sesame seeds over the bun. It all makes a total taste of western culture, which, as the name suggests, was the intention. PURPOSE WELL SERVED.

I enjoyed my meal. HOWEVER\xe2\x80\xa6YEAH I KNOW!!! The burger doesn't look as good as it does in pictures (Sounds familiar? I know it doesn't only happen when you go on a date with someone you met on the internet after getting smitten with their heavily filtered photos BUT it also happens when you buy food based on the enticing pictures) and not fulfilling on quantity, you have to order fries with it. 

Another thing that I read some reviews that it wasn't pocket friendly, I would say it is pretty reasonable compared to other burger chains' burgers. It is Rs. 390 (separately) which I think is okay.

8/10.

Verdict: Have a try, you won't regret.'

b"\xf0\x9f\x8c\xaf Shawarmas from PITA - The Shawarma Revolution

Regular typical shawarma is just too mainstream now. It's always good to try something new, so I tried Kolachi and Original Beiruti Shawarma from Pita. I love to explore new flavours and I've noticed that usually shawarma has a typical flavour at every place. Fortunately, you can try different types of shawarmas here. :D
Okay, so I liked Kolachi more as compared to Original Beiruti. Both were scrumptious and juicy, they were filled with enormous amount of meat. 
Original Beiruti had a filling of meat, fries, pickles and of course, their special delicious sauce. 
Kolachi had a filling of meat, onions, tomatoes and their special sauce to enhance the flavour. 
Moreover, another good thing about their shawarma is that they wrapped it up in flatbread instead of pita bread. It's a healthier option, I loved it!"

b"So yesterday after waiting a long while, got a chance to attend sea food festival and that too at my favourite hotel - Avari! It was our anniversary and I wanted to make it extra special for my wifey. Keeping in mind, we are both prawn and fish lovers, we went to the festival at Asia live and man, we were so full and super happy when we got done there. 
Started off with soup seafood bisque, which had a very balanced flavour and totally geared us up for what was coming our way. Appetisers main, our personal favourite were the saffron prawns as they were fried and just so crisp, we couldn't have enough of them!
The salad bar was a delight to even look at, so many colours and a galore of various textures and flavours! From prawn lettuce wraps to dynamite prawns;assorted cheese to crab salad- everything was not only tempting but way too delicious. But kitna khaatay? Main course was left! 
In desi, my personal favourite was the fish biryani! Just the way we love it! Other than that, brilliantly made crab yellow curry reminded me of some of the best Thai restaurants I've visited. Fish on skewers had a unique taste to it, pan fried tuna steak was light and so refreshing! My wife likes Italian so she loveddd pasta marinara. Not to forget, there was a variety of fish to choose from and they made spicy red snapper there and then for me. 
Desserts were heaven melting in mouth like always but the best was their blueberry cheesecake! 
Wonderful experience in all, I would give 10/10 as it was not only yummy but their service is awesome and we were absolutely content by the end of it!"

b"Milestone Super Market (Cafe).  After being jaded by overpriced and overcooked eggs served by literally every place in the city, I have started seeking value. I'm done with those random stale rocket leaves, and those pretty (but bland) plates.

Milestone has a basic breakfast menu.  Eggs of whatever type, and coffee at a super price.  Mushroom and Cheese Omelette for like PKR 200, and decent coffee for another PKR 250.  One can have a solid breakfast for PKR 450.  Grab a fresh baguette, and you can be done as well.

No frills, no bullshit, no stupid filters -- just decent breakfast.  Go for a quick breakfast, and avoid pretentious andas elsewhere.  

Also, they serve a mean pizza -- the old school type."

b'After reading good reviews about #shisi,  I decided to dine there a few days back.  Belive me the reviews did justice . Starting from the ambiance which gave a very refreshing feel , mainly because of the interior colour and plantation. The manager was very welcoming and kind enough to guide us throughout (this is done by every chain,  but few extra efforts are always appreciable) .The menu was very detailed , and a great variety to choose from , After the help of reviews and staff recommendation ,
We orderd their coconut soup, tom tung goong (my all time fav:D) , DYNAMITE PRAWNS,  siracha chicken,  Mongolian beef , pad thai spicy noodles ,thai red curry , garlic rice and egg fried rice.
The serving size was good enough that even a single serving could be shared. Writing about the over all food experience rather than individual dishes : presentation, serving size , flavours , aroma,service and yes the FOOODD was all 5 star \xe2\x99\xa1 
We were served with complimentary nutella cake which was like cherry on the top  :D 

I would recommend you all to go and try out , 
Per head was around 1300. 
Thankyou team #shisi'

b'Located in a quiet setting away from the hustle and noise of K-town, Coco 9 is a quaint little spot to get your caffeine fix and grab a light snack. We loved this place for its attention to aesthetics and excellent coffee. 

The cafe is bright and open. There is a minimal Scandinavian vibe married with wood. The variety of plants spruce up the place with some life and relaxation. 

Fantastic coffee. Rich and creamy cup of earthy roast of cappuccino. Perfect for that early evening pick me up.

Decent sandwiches. Whilst the menu was not extensive per se, I did just wonder if there could have been a bit more variety.

Featuring a wide array of artisanal pastries and desserts, the sweet treats were created more as a feast for the eyes than for the palate. 

Overall, a great find. Definitely worth a visit!'

For the love of nutella we had nutella wontons. They were served with a scoop of icecream. Though I liked the rasberry cheese cake because of its blastic salty sour and sweet flavors! 
This journey of trying all asian cuisine went good! I might now often sit at such bistros just to taste the very unique flavors of chinese japanese korean thai and wat not..  to get a break from  desi food. Will definetely go back to try more of their dishes!'

b'Todays review
*soi asian bistro*
Location : khayaban e saher
Its a beautiful and comfortable place for a perfect bistro experience. I was overwhelmed to see the menu and the amount of cuisines they are serving. It was hard for me to choose from the menu because i wanted to try almost everything korean thai chinese japanese and what not! 
The servers were quite courteous. Finally on recommendation i ordered
Wasabi prawns: fresh good sized prawns with a perfect crunchy coating drizzled with the magical wasabi sauce, Not to little no to much.
Korean beef bowl: The item to fall in love with the look of it. A bowl of rice served with perfectly marinated slices of beef and served with veges, sunny side up eggs and spicy sweet sauce with it which had its own unique hotness.the sesame seeds sprinkled over the egg gave it a next level look.
Oriental spicy noodles: instant love as i love spicy food . It had a tangy flavour and had bite size chicken pieces in it.the noodles were cooked to perfection. 
Golden pie: the balance of sweetness and salt blew me off. It was a perfect dessert choice to end my meal with! 
Enjoyed my experience! This place has become my choice for the asian cuisine from now onwards since the textures and flavors won me for sure.'

b"I recently paid a visit to Market - Modern Asian Kitchen with a few friends. It is a nice cosy restaurant located in Bukhari commercial near chotu chai wala. After looking at the menu I could see why they named it market because a lot of the items on their menu gave that 'asian street food' kinda vibe, which is right up my alley!

We started with loaded kimchi fries, steamed shrimp dumplings in chilli oil and chicken satay with spicy peanut sauce. The fries were an absolute winner for me! Fully loaded with shredded Korean beef, cheese and kimchi. It was truly a party in my mouth. 
This was my first experience with dumplings and I'm totally addicted. The dumplings were cooked to perfection and that chilli oil really brought the whole dish together.

From the sushi menu we tried the fire roll, paradise roll and the Karachi roll (crispy California). The sushi tasted really fresh and completely melted in the month. Compared to other sushi places their price is really economical for the food and quantity they provide. 

From the mains we tried the fire cracker chicken with jasmine rice, Korean fried chicken sliders with spicy gochujang sauce and steamed bao buns. All 3 mains were outstanding especially the Korean sliders, the fried chicken in it was so so crispy! And that spicy sauce really complemented the sliders. 

For dessert we ordered the crying chocolate. I'm a meetha freak and for me it hit all the right spots. It wasn't too sweet because of the unsweetened cocoa powder sprinkled on top. It was served with vanilla ice cream and the whole plate was wiped clean in under 10 seconds. 

I would also like to mention that the staff was really friendly and the service was spot on. So if you're in the mood for a modern twist on asian street food, you know where to go :)"

b"Desi Guy Review for Chop Chop Wok

Tried many times, but reviewing them for the first time. Chop chop wok's pan asian in brown rice is my all time favourite. 

Well this time we ordered;

1- Ramen 

This dish went beyond my expectations, I had tried schezwan version of Ramen in Europe before, but this was different from original and had nice taste of all ingredients mixed together. Usually boiled chicken used in ramen but they have used grilled chicken with sauce on it. Overall noodles, chicken, mushroom and veges complimenting each other to make a good combination. 

2- Fire Cracker Chicken

Spicy chicken cubes with brown rice, though this dish was common but was soothing with rice. Suggestion add little gravy to it. 

3- Black pepper Beef

This was again common dish, as many other restaurants are playing well with pepper beef. 
Although beef was tender and onions were complimenting the over all taste of the dish. 

4- Fried Ice Cream 

My all time favourite dessert dish, vanilla flavour ice cream scoop dipped with nuts and fried, topped with chocolate liquid. 

Total damage including 3 drinks, 2700pkr."

b"Rant against foodpanda and BurgerLab:
My colleagues and I placed an order through foodpanda for BurgerLab today. The online order was placed somewhat around 12 or 12:15 PM. When the foodpanda representative called to confirm, due to some misunderstanding the order was cancelled. I immediately wrote to their online support to confirm the order, I even asked if they would confirm it like this or would I have to re-order. As seen from the screenshots, their representative confirmed the order and ensured it would be delivered by 1:24 PM.
An hour over their designated time, I inquired again only to find that they had confused another order which was also placed from our office through foodpanda for Chop Chop Wok and considered our BurgerLab order as delivered (despite my mentioning our BurgerLab order no#). The foodpanda representative called and proposed that I place an order AGAIN (this was at 2:30 PM). 
I didn't take the risk of an online order this time and directly called foodpanda and placed my order. I requested them to deliver the order as soon as possible as everyone was SUPER HUNGRY by that time. They assured they will. Our order arrived at 4:15 PM. We were STARVED. The cherry on top was that the order was WRONG (also the burgers were cold and the fries were stale and rubbery). We called BurgerLab to complain, they said they'll listen to the call recording of our order and get back to us. They called 10 minutes later and admitted their mistake, their representative mistakenly told us of a different flavor (Big Bang) which was not part of the deal we ordered. They said they'll send us the order we want but they'll deduct the bill from their representative's salary (the one who handled our order). We said we didn't want that (who would have a meal at the cost of a poor man's salary?).
Bottom line is that the service we got from both foodpanda and BurgerLab was extremely poor. Foodpanda was irresponsible (didn't bother to check our order no# and confused the order only to let us know too late that it was cancelled) whereas BurgerLab shamelessly played the guilt card. 
Money- ruined
Mood- ruined
Appetite- ruined
THANKS A BUNCH! #Foodpanda #BurgerLab"

b"#TSGBLOGGERTEHNIAT

Eatery: Moos 'n' Clucks (Gulshan e Iqbal)

Overall experience: 7/10

We had been planning to give Moos N Clucks a visit since quite some time but our busy schedules just didn't allow us till recently.

Located in Gulshan e Iqbal near Disco Bakery, this place was easy to find. However, parking can be a bit difficult since it's a busy area.

Upon reaching, we found the place packed and we thanked heavens for our reservation which allowed us to be seated right away. 

What we ordered:

Chicken Cheese Poppers Rs 220
Cottage Fries Rs 160
Beasts Fries Rs 160
Mac N Cheese Bunless Burger Rs 340
Portland Winner Rs 260
Gooey Bleu Rs 280
Jalapeno Royale Rs 260

My favourite among these were Portland Winner in beef and Gooey Bleu in Chicken. From appetizers, Chicken Cheese Poppers stole the show!

Chicken Cheese Poppers were fried chicken strips filled with cheddar cheese and topped with mustard honey sauce. The chicken was flavorsome. It was a messy eat though and you'd better have napkins nearby when trying these \xf0\x9f\x98\x89

Cottage Fries were the regular cheese fries we get anywhere else whereas Beast Fries were topped with minced meat, jalapenos and olives! 

Mac N Cheese Bunless Burger: 
Not something I had looked forward to. I felt there was room for improvement in both the Mac N Cheese and the beef patty. The beef could've had been juicier. But whoever likes this combination will probably love it.

Jalapeno Royale wasn't as good as I had expected. The Jalapeno sauce overpowered the taste of beef. 

Gooey Bleu was my favourite among the four I tried. The chicken was tender and flavoursome, and cheese oozed at every bite. 

Portland Winner: The beef patty could've been a bit more juicy otherwise it was good. The sauces complemented the burger.  

Taste: 3/5
Quality: 3.5/5
Quantity: 3/5
Presentation: 3/5
Price: 4/5"

b"EGGNOG with Qarshi Johar Joshanda

Eggnog Recipe:

What You'll Need:
6 large eggs
2 egg yolks
1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar
1/4 teaspoon salt
4 cups milk (whole)
1 tablespoon vanilla extract
1 tablespoon Johar Joshanda
1/2 teaspoon nutmeg (grated)
1/4 cup heavy cream (whipped to soft peaks)
Garnish: Additional grated nutmeg

How to Make It:
Combine eggs, egg yolks, sugar,Johar Joshanda and salt in a heavy 3- or 4-quart pan, whisking until well-combined.
Continue whisking while pouring milk in a slow, steady stream until completely incorporated.
Turn on burner to lowest possible heat setting.
Place pan on burner and stir mixture continuously until an instant-read thermometer reaches 160 F and the mixture thickens enough to coat the back of a spoon. Be patient. This should take about 45 to 60 minutes.
Strain mixture through a fine sieve into a large bowl to remove any accidental small cooked bits of egg.
Add vanilla extract and nutmeg, stirring to combine.
Pour into a glass pitcher, decanter, or container and cover with a lid or plastic wrap. Refrigerate this egg custard mixture to chill at least 4 hours or up to 3 days before finishing.
When ready to serve, pour heavy cream into a bowl and whip until it forms soft peaks. Fold whipped cream into cold custard mixture until combined.
Serve eggnog in chilled cups or glasses and garnish with a sprinkle of nutmeg.

#joharjoshanda #sehatkaflavor #eggnog #fusion #recipecompetition"

b"Shisi-Pan Asian Bistro. 
A small cozy place at the SMCHS. The Ambiance is pretty good. 4\xc3\x97 Platters of fresh crispy crackers were served immediately. The little serving of the spicy kimchi-like veggies was unique.
We ordered a family bowl of their Hot & Sour soup. The serving was enough for a total of 8 people. We requested them to reheat the leftover soup and serve it later when the rest of the people arrive and they were courteous enough to do so. The soup had generous amount of vegetables and seasonings but it wasn't 'hot' enough.  
We a ordered a total of 4 main courses. 
Chicken Sriracha-Was moderately spicy.
Cherry Chicken- Boneless chicken pieces in a toothsome sweet and tangy sauce.
Prawns with Chilli Sauce- The star of the show for me. Perfectly cooked fresh prawns in a spicy sauce with saut\xc3\xa8ed onions. 
The rice bowls- They were all fresh and perfectly seasoned rice. You get free refills so at Shisi you don't have to worry about the quantity of rice. 
Chicken Chowmein- Made up of normal spaghetti instead of egg noodles. They were generous with the protein and the vegetables.

For desert they had the choice of nutella and/or fudge cake. 

Before we left, the manager came and inquired about our experience. 

Overall a 4.5 star experience. The prices are reasonable.

Scream-
Located right next to Shisi at SMCHS. Even though we loved the Ice-Creams and the Boba Ice Teas, I would say that the place was over priced. 
We tried their freshly frozen peach,mango and chocolate flavour for 250/- each. Even though the quantity was less but the quality wasn't compromised. 
Now the Boba Iced Tea. 
The menu stated that the Boba Iced Tea was priced at Rs.250/-. We ordered Lychee/Blueberry and PineApple/Blueberry. 
The iced tea was the right temperature and full of flavour. 
The Bobas are tiny balls full of the flavour you choose. They burst in your mouth, splashing the flavour!
When we got the bill, we found out that only the Iced Tea was priced at 250. The Bobas were considered as a topping and we were charged Rs.50/- extra per drink.
Well, the drink was worth it but they should mention that in the menu. 

The staff was humble and nice.

3.5 stars for Scream."

b"So guys here is my recipe for this interesting #SehatKaFlavor competition by Qarshi Johar Joshanda.

Decadent Slow Cooker Hot Chocolate with Marshmallows & Chocolate Johar Joshanda \xf0\x9f\x8f\x86\xe2\x98\x95\xf0\x9f\x8d\xab\xf0\x9f\x8c\xbe\xf0\x9f\x8c\xbf\xf0\x9f\x8d\x83\xf0\x9f\x8e\x81\xf0\x9f\x92\x96

Ingredients:
6 cups whole milk 
2 cups heavy cream
1/2 cup granulated sugar
8 ounces semi-sweet chocolate, coarsely chopped
1/4 cup unsweetened natural cocoa powder
2 teaspoons pure vanilla extract
1 Sachet Johar Joshanda Chocolate
toppings: marshmallows

Directions:

Place all of the ingredients into a large pan.
Vigorously whisk to get the cocoa powder as mixed in as possible-- you don't want it all floating on the top. Keep whisking for a minute or 2 until it's all combined.
Cook on low for an hours. Make sure you whisk it every 15 minutes to make sure the chocolate isn't burning on the bottom.
Remove from heat and add a sachet of Johar Joshanda Chocolate to get that minty flavour.
Serve warm with marshmallows on top. Store leftovers in the refrigerator and warm up on the stove or in the microwave.

#SehatKaFlavor #JoharJoshanda #HotDrink"

b'#JoharJoshanda #SehatKaFlavor #Competition
Chicken Vegetable Joshanda #Soup 
prep 15 minscook 30 minstotal 45 mins

Ingredients
1 whole chicken (or a few chicken legs or chicken breasts)
3-4 ribs of celery
3-4 large carrots
2 medium onions
5-6 garlic cloves
1 pack of Johar Joshanda Classic or Suger Free.
any other vegetables you have around and want to add
5-6 eggs, beaten in a bowl
cayenne pepper
sea salt
pepper
garlic powder (optional)

Instructions
Boil chicken in large pot until cooked. (Note: If using chicken breast instead of whole chicken, chicken broth can be used in place of water). Remove cooked chicken from water and chop into small pieces.
Add chopped celery, carrots, onions, and garlic cloves to boiling water. Add sea salt, pepper and garlic or herbs. I add 1-2 TBSP of each except cayenne, which I add about 1/2 tsp or to taste.
Boil until vegetables are cooked. Add a sachet of #JoharJoshanda Sugar Free.  While stirring, add beaten eggs slowly so that they distribute (it will look similar to egg drop soup). Boil 2 minutes until eggs are cooked, remove from heat and serve.'

b"Do you hate money?
Do you hate waiters who get your order right the first time?
Do you hate your tastebuds?

Then head on down to Newbury Cafe, the coolest new eatery in town with no substance, taste or standard of service.

Medium well is just a figure of speech. The cook knows what we really meant was rare (or raw?).

The secret to cooking good chicken is to cook the shit out of it until it's cardboard dry. You want it so that it sucks all the moisture out of your mouth. Only good restaurants do that.

Also the only place in Karachi to bring us complimentary bengan. Yes, literal \xf0\x9f\x8d\x86.

Great place to take selfies though.

Warning: the tears welling up in your eyes after paying 1800 rs. per head may potentially ruin said selfie but oh look at the interior, so light and airy. If only I could eat the ambience."

b"#TSGBloggerSMH

Koffie Chalet: A quick fix for a refreshing taste and wonderful customer service :-)

#SMHpoints: 8.5/10

Breakfast is the most important meal of the day, and when an eatery makes it special and perfect for you the whole day becomes amazing. This is what Koffie Chalet has always done by providing not only good food but amazing customer service. 
We went there early morning around 8:30 and used our Vouch365 for breakfast. We ordered Stuffed Chicken Strips with fries as the sideline and Chalet special breakfast with cheese balls as sideline. 

Here's the review:

#ChaletSpecialBreakfast: Tender beef steak wrapped in feta cheese and filled omelette, this beauty with a side line of cheese balls and bran bread was just love. Each bite you could feel the cheese oozing out and blasting in your mouth with the tender meaty flavor blended in by the beef steak. The cheese balls were a cherry on the top filled with huge amounts of cheese, this special was just outstanding.
Price: Pkr 847

#StuffedChickenSteak: badumtusshhhh, hands down I'm in love. Tender chicken stuffed with creamy cheese topped with feta cheese and served with a sideline of fries, this one was an explosion of the taste buds if you're a cheese lover. Loved it.
Price: Pkr 725

Service and Ambiance: Well the customer service as usual was spot on, we used our Vouch365 for the order and our koffie chalet reward card. They were very accommodating with our requests and the ambiance was pretty good considering it was well lit with some decoration as well.
4/5

Food: 8.5/10
Taste: 8.5/10
Value for money: 8.5/10
Ambiance: 8/10
Customer Service: 8.5/10

#Total: 42/50"

b"I went to Sobremesa last night with my family to celebrate my mother's birthday and they perfectly ruined it for us, here's how:

When we reached the place, they told us they're fully occupied and asked us to wait for 20 minutes. The place was compact and there was no sitting arrangement in the waiting area (Actually there was no waiting area either, we had to stand at the entrance while waiting). 
We had to wait for 45 minutes before we got a spot. After that, nobody was there to serve us for at least 15 minutes. We kept calling the waiters/managers but no one showed up. A waiter came after 15 minutes, we asked him to guide us about some of the dishes in the menu. Unfortunately, the didn't know anything and took a while to read the description as he was clueless. 

Now coming to the food:
We ordered:
1. Deep dish pizza: Wasn't what we had expected. The crust on the boundary and the base of the pizza, was too thick. NOT RECOMMENDED!
2. Dry chicken chilli: It was really spicy as there was a bunch of green chillies. 
3. Sandwich: didn't like the taste.
4. Fettuccine alfredo: It was bearable.
5. Strawberry lemonade: Regret ordering it, it was rather a strawberry slush.

To our surprise, they didn't even pack the left over pizza for us. Everything else was there but no pizza (There was more than a slice left)

Quantity: The serving was extremely less and disappointing. Each dish would serve approximately only one person. 
Taste: It was okay-ish.
Service: PATHETIC!

We had two vouchers of Vouch365, through which we planned to avail 100% free servings of Penne Marinara and beef chilli dry, but instead, they provided 99% discount and charged us 1% for the free items.

Conclusion:
The place is overpriced and over-hyped. Never visiting again."

status_message:
b"The Kentucky Burger (KFC) \xf0\x9f\x8d\x94 looks great in poster/ marketing campaign but is the Kentucky Burger really worth trying \xf0\x9f\xa4\x94? Let me break it down for you guys. A juicy Original Crispy (Zinger Style) fillet but bigger in size, crispy onions on top , slice of cheese, pepperoni and smoky BBQ sauce. Oooh yeah! \xf0\x9f\x98\x8e Almost everything a burger fanatic wants, \xe2\x9c\x8b\xf0\x9f\x8f\xbbOH WAIT! I forgot to mention the fancy bun that gives it a really BADASS look. My experience with Kentucky Burger was really pleasant as everything was nearly perfect the aroma of bbq sauce \xf0\x9f\x99\x88, the crisp of zinger patty mixed with crispy onions \xe2\x9d\xa4\xef\xb8\x8fplus that yummy pepperoni on the top OH MAMA MIA \xf0\x9f\x98\x8d. Every burger \xf0\x9f\x98\x81 Oppsi I mean BURGER LOVERS should give it a try. Size is bit small \xf0\x9f\x92\x94 as compared to the price but taste balances that flaw. Finally KFC got something right \xf0\x9f\x91\x8d btw according to my experience KFC's taste varies over branches I tried at North Nazimabad Branch in a really slow slot so they served it hot & perfect. As burger has lots of layers I won't recommend it for take away or delivery. 

PS: KFC sucks in takeaway & delivery anyway \xf0\x9f\x98\x88. 

Conclusion: | Presentation: 8/10 | Taste: 8.5/10 | Worth For Money: 8/10 | A must try \xe2\x9c\x85"

b"I went to Zauq located in Dolmen Mall Clifton yesterday to try their newly launched Hi Tea Buffet
I visited zauq back in Ramadan for iftaar and really loved the food which is why I just had to come back to try the hi tea. I was pleasantly surprised to see they had set up a whole area for a birthday party in the restaurant (a fully decorated space which looked amazeballs- had no idea they do these sorts of arrangements).
Anyway I tried the hot n sour soup, Kachori with aloo (pls tell me the correct name for this bhujia sort of thing), pasta, Fried rice, chicken manchurian, fried fish, shawarma roll, cupcake, jalebi, and gulab jamun.
About the soup, I have had better hot n sour soup but it was a good start to the meal and I'm glad it had just the right amount of spice (didn't add anything to it). I don't recommend having too much because there's a lot of variety so you will feel full quicker and probably wont be able to try everything.
The Kachori and aloo were spot on. I'm no desi food expert but i've had plenty and these were pretty good, although I just wish the Kachori was a little warmer. 
The pasta was quite nice, had a tomato based sauce and was garmished with cheese and herbs. YUM.
The rice and manchurian as you can see, I mixed (very typical of me I agree HAHA). It was pretty good. The chicken was well cooked and the gravy thankfully didn't taste like ketchup saalan.
I don't generally like fish but the shaadion wali fried fish is always to die for (nothing healthy here hahaha). This fish too, was delectable and fresh. It wasn't over-coated or over greasy (ya know, wasn't a little tukra of machli inside a large cocoon of flour). I quite liked it on it's own, didn't want to dip into sauce (I hope the sauce I very nicely ignored was tartar and not just mayonnaise).
The shawarma type roll-thingy wasn't like authentic shawarma but rather had a mayonnaise type taste. It didn't taste bad at all, i'd just rather call it a pita roll rather than a shawarma lol.
At this point I was full to the brim but had to try the desserts so let me just say this cupcake was no ordinary sookha hua anday ki smell wala cupcake, it was actually pretty good. I went back for another (guilty as charged).
Pakistani restaurants are always killin it with the piping hot gulaab jamuns so need I say more???? 10/10
As you can tell I couldn't stop laughing because everyone was being served hot, crispy jalebis on their tables amidst their meals but truth be told, they tasted good (couldn't have more than one bite warna waheen heart attack hojata).
I really liked how the manager went twice/ thrice to each table to ask if everything was fine and there were no issues. They were serving unlimited refills of peach juice which is quite nice.

The Hi Tea buffet costs 799 plus tax per person which adds up to around 900 pkr. Is it worth it? Yes! And sit next to the windows to have your meal with a view. And have little amounts of everything so you can try everything. And don't have lunch before you go!"

b"Review regarding the new eatery in town. LAMOSH CHAE
We had 
2 Beef Pizza Burgers. (Rs 800) 
1 Beef Classic Burger. (Rs 350) 
2 Chicken Pizza Fries. (500) 
4 Soft Drinks. (280) 
Total Cost :  1930
Everything was Amazing. 
Hats Off To Them. 

Pizza Burger is surely challenging to complete. Because after finishing it, only I myself know that how I finished my Chicken Pizza Fries. 
Pizza burger currently isn't mentioned in their menu card. But yes they have written it specifically on a board. As it is introduced just 3 days ago. 
Chicken Pizza Fries were another delight to have. Gentle amount of cheese, olives and pickles. 

Taste 10/10
Service 9/10
Ambiance 6/10
(They just need to work on their ambiance a bit. Or just simply make a boundary or something) 

Photos may not look good. But believe me the taste was thousand times better which you might guess by looking at the photos. 
Management was very corporative  specially Shahbaz Bhai as I know him from few years."

b"Recently had dinner TavernGrill Karachi with family.
We ordered:

*Crusted Parmesan Chicken with includes a bowl of delicious pasta with 2 crusted chicken steaks and pesto sauce to die for. Hands down to the best Chicken parma in K-Town. Score 10/10

*Chicken Panini with fries and coleslaw, another delicious dish which we tried for the first time and weren't disappointed. Score 9/10.

*Chicken Alfredo Pasta, unfortunately their pasta was a bit bland this time but usually it has more flavour. Score 6/10.

*Chicken Tarragon (Steak) with spicy brown rice as a sideline was also a first for us and it was delicious. The chicken was tender and full of flavours, the rice were well-balanced in flavours and well cooked. Score 9/10.

*Also their Chicken Quesadilla, which was also delicious and was gone before I could take a picture \xf0\x9f\x98\x82 Score 9/10.

However, the service was a bit slow due to PSL match that day \xf0\x9f\x98\x82 but the overall experience was good."

b'I ordered their PSL deal " Zalmi".I am a huge fan of their Chicken Tikka pizza. It is just fabulous. That flavor is a constant. 
The main thing is the crust and topping of the pizza which i really focus on. Their pizza, whenever it arrives, is hot and fresh with a crispy crust. Sometimes if there is any leftover and i microwave it the second day, its still tastes amazing. The amount of cheese, chicken and veggies put on the pizza is pretty good as well.

Being a local pizza joint is not easy, you have to compete with the local giants as well as the other pizza parlors. And among those if someone gives you the value for money, taste and good service, then thats it. They have made themselves a customer for a long time!! \xf0\x9f\x98\x80
Cheers!!
they gifted free bat too.#PizzaPoint'

b"Junaidi's Pizza..

Ordered 3 large za's.. the ricotta spinach, pepperoni and the chicken. 

The beautiful thing about this little pizzeria is that it knows how to do pizza right and it knows you dont need to have  32 flavors under the sun to do it.

I've been blessed to eat authentic wood burner over pizza when we would meet up with our friends at the italian consulate and the ricotta spinach pizza brought back fond memories of pizza al italia..

the chicken would have been brilliant with soke more ragu and perhaps a bit of rocket thrown on.. but i honestly cannot fault it

3 large pies set us back 3200 bucks and fed 5 adults and 4 kids.. and we all loved em...

Junaidi .. whoever you are.. great Job!"

b"#TSGBLOGGERTEHNIAT

Eatery: Ranoush Villa

Overall experience: 8/10

Karachi is famous for its blooming food industry and budding restaurants are giving a tough competition to the old ones. Ranoush Villa took this chance to bring even better delicacies and ambiance for its customers and stand out amongst the crowd.  

A new menu, better ambiance, and impeccable service was what we were provided with on our last visit.

We started with their Tomato Basil Soup that left us totally impressed. Each ingredient was balanced perfectly with none overpowering the other. It wouldn't be wrong to call it comfort food. We had their freshly baked garlic bread as well which was spot on. 

Fajita Nachos were next on our to-try list and not exaggerating but they were the best I have ever had. They had a generous amount of chicken and cheese, and remained crispy till the end. If you're looking for the best nachos, Ranoush is the place to be. 

Mozzarella Cheese Balls were served next. We like ours cheesier so we conveyed the message to the chef himself as well as the co-owner Mr Ansar who was hearing our feedback with all ears. 

For main courses, we had their Entrecote Steak, Moroccan Chicken, Cashew Nut Chicken, Spaghetti Shrimps Pasta and Crispy Stuffed Burger. Of these Spaghetti Shrimps Pasta and Crispy Stuffed Burger stole the show. 

The Spaghetti Shrimp Pasta was absolutely divine. It was a bit spicy for us but we loved it. The shrimps were well-cooked and the dish was thoroughly enjoyable and bursting with flavours.

Crispy Stuffed Burger was one of the best we have had here in Karachi. The beef was juicy and well-marinated with a generous amount of cheese. Not too much. Not too little. The buns, too, were baked in house and we were glad they could hold all the meat and cheese without crumbling down which is what happens at most burger places.

Followed by the main courses came the desserts and they looked just beautiful! They were so tempting that we did not feel like spoiling the fantastic presentation. As expected, the temptation got the better of us and we devoured them to the last bite.

Frosted brownie and cookie were served with vanilla ice cream. They were such a perfect combination of hot and cold dessert. We particularly loved the hot chocolate oozing out from the cookie.

Taste: 7/10
Quality: 7.5/10
Quantity: 8/10
Price: 7/10
Menu Selection: 8/10

Location: 4/5
Ambiance: 4/5
Service: 4/5
Presentation: 5/5
Hygiene: 4/5"

b"#TSGBLOGGERNIDAABBAS
Eatery: Shisi- Pan Asian Bistro

 I am sure you must have heard the name. It's a causal dine in for authentic Chinese,Thai and Japanese cuisine.  This restaurant is located in the heart of Karachi at Sindhi Muslim. The interior of this restaurant is extremely beautiful!! Clearly shows how much they've had worked on this restaurant's set up. They even provide valet parking which is a blessing considering it's location.

Let's start with the starters. We were served the following items:
Spicy Coconut Soup
Kimchi  Dip
Dynamite Prawns
Thread Chicken

Spicy Coconut Soup:
The soup consisted of intense and aromatic flavours with rich and creamy coconut infused broth. It's not just a treat to the taste buds but in fact visually beautiful too. A perfect balanced of texture and taste!!

Kimchi Dip:
Kimchi used to be one of the best things they had available at all good restaurants in Hong Kong. It's a staple in Korean cuisine. The kimchi they had here had the correct spice, tanginess and a bit of sweet was a complete seller!! 

Dynamite Prawns:
Perfectly battered fried prawns tossed with honey mayo chilli glaze, the prawns they are serving are literally one of its kind!! I was lost for words when I took the first bite!! This appetizer literally UP-ed the game! A friend said they tasted similar to the ones she had at P.F Chang's. 

Thread Chicken:
This appetizer was new for me, I am sure many of the people know about this already since it's very common in ramzan. Thread Chicken was very tender from the inside and crunchy on the outside!! The flavour of the chicken sort of reminded me of kfc's chicken BUT 'A LOT BETTER VERSION.'

We were served the following entrees:
Sriracha Chicken
Crispy Beef
Mongolian Chicken 
Vegetable Fried Rice 
 Egg Fried Rice 
Garlic Fried Rice 
Nutella Cake 

Sriracha Chicken:
Sriracha Chicken is basically a mixture of sweet & spicy flavors. If you are like me and crave for some good spicy food then you should go to shisi today and try this out!! 

Crispy Beef:
This was the star of the evening! Right amount of crisp with extremely juicy flavourful beef inside! It was one dish I couldn't stop myself from eating.

Mongolian Chicken:
Moderately spiced, crispy, sweet chicken coated with this addictive sweet/salty sauce which was extremely delicious with some vegetable rice. Was this my favourite on the menu? No. Would I still eat it? YES! 

Coming To The Rice:
When you order a bowl of rice here you just have to pay for one serving and the refills are free of cost. You can eat as much as rice you would like. How cool is that? I love how the egg and vegetable rice had freshness to it, whereas garlic rice was the only thing I wouldn't swear by. My friend surely enjoyed her share of garlic rice but when it comes to me I would prefer vegetable rice over it. 

Nutella Cake:
Anything that has Nutella can never ever go wrong. Am I right? We were served a slice of their famous Nutella cake and I kid you not, one single bite took me right into food coma. The picture does not do justice to how delicious it was!

Verdict:
Over all experience was amazing and I would really recommend everyone to give this place a try it's like we have this amazing place so nearby and we've missed out on it!

Rating: 
Taste: (8/10)
Quantity: (8/10)
Presentation: (7.5/10)
Service: (7.5/10)"

b"#TSGBLOGGERTEHNIAT

Del Frio (SMCHS)

Saturday breakfast at Del Frio; an absolute delight even though the service was super slow. 

What we ordered?
Bread basket -> Complimentary
Roma Eggs Rs 560
Del Frio's Special Omelette Rs 435
Mushroom Chicken Burger Rs 520
Soft drink Rs 95

Bread basket was fresh.

I had Roma eggs for myself which came with focaccia topped with turkey slices and cheese omelette. It was one of the best breakfasts I've had at Del Frio. The turkey was full of flavour. Omelette was actually cheesy and the pesto sauce complemented the bread and eggs!

Del Frio's Special Omelette hardly had any chicken or seasoning but when we brought this to their attention they replaced it right away. The new one was excellent. 

Mushroom burger looked tempting but I didn't try it neither did I hear anything negative about it. So yeap, thumbs up for that. 

Used our Bogo PK voucher so got a breakfast free on purchase of one. Total bill for 3 was Rs 1384. 

The service was pretty slow. The server was inattentive and missed our order of dessert. 

Coming to the ambiance, there were too many mosquitoes. When asked to spray we were told that it would make it more difficult for us to sit. \xf0\x9f\x98\x95 

Taste: 4/5
Quality: 4/5
Quantity: 4/5
Price: 4/5
Presentation: 3.5/5
Service: 3/5
Ambiance: 2.5/5

Overall experience: 7/10"

b"#TSGBloggerSMH
Not a review but a message

So the free burger posts of foodpanda are popping up today and all of them say that a PSLUBL20 code has been used. Well foodpanda just highlighted that this was a glitch on their system due to which a 20% discount was being calculated as a 100% discount.
We feel sorry for foodpanda as one can't imagine the amount of loss they wouldve faced due to this and for the general public we would just like to highlight a couple of things:

1- No eatery or service offers a 100% discount on just one item order and it is highly unlikely that you will pay Rs.90 or 200 only for 6-7 burgers each of which are worth around 500-600 each. So in such cases its actually a better option if you can verify from the eatery about the discount as we know one can have the guilt of other having a loss.
 
2- This is targetted towards the people who comment and often use harsh words unknowingly. When someone posts about such things please avoid using harsh words against them as they didn't know about the issue and even if they did you're no one to judge. We've a very rude mindset amongst our nation in which we act as judge jury and executioner. Even I was targeted today by one such gentleman who called me a robber not because I had availed the discount but because I had highlighted and clarified the issue.

Point being, don't use harsh words just like  that. There's always a polite way to get your point across. Also stop judging people over petty things."

b"#TSGBLOGGERHAMZA 

Eatery: Cafe Bistrovia

Verdict: A cozy place for an economical, yet nice family food outing. 

Overall Rating: 8/10

Located opposite the planetarium, bustling amongst the ever-so food street of university road, Caf\xc3\xa9 Bistrovia is a restaurant that is hard to miss. A large, bright yellow logo with an attractive bold font that catches the eye instantly. 

A group of 3 food mongers ordered what seemed to be the best on their menu: Smoked BBQ Beef and Bacon Burger, The Bistrovia Beef Burger (both burgers served with an extra patty), and Chicken Alfredo Pasta. 

Overall ratings: 

Taste: 8/10

Quality: 8/10

Quantity: 8.5/10

Ambiance: 7/10

Location: 7/10

Hygiene: 8.5/10

Value for Money: 9/10

Cost: Roughly PKR 550/- per head (including extra patty and a drink!)

Starting off with the burgers \xe2\x80\x93 Smoked BBQ Beef and Bacon Burger: PLEASE BEFORE YOU JUMP YOUR SEATS, Bacon is not pork it is simply a specific type of meat cut prepared on a grill. No one in Pakistan serves Pork Bacon. This was halal, cow meat. Anyway, as you can probably see from the pictures, the double patty burger is monstrosity at its best. 120-gram double patties, topped with cheddar cheese, iceberg, bacon and a very flavorful Smoked BBQ sauce. The burger was pure beauty. The patty was fresh, it wasn't breaking, it was firm, cooked rightfully on the grill and juicy most importantly. The bun was also not soggy and seemed as if baked right this morning. A good burger always satisfies my hungry tummy, and this one was a winner. 

I had the chance to also taste the Bistrovia Beef burger \xe2\x80\x93 it was a classic beef burger topped with a ripe piece of tomato and some of their own made sauces. Giant, and juicy. Served with an electric lemonade on the side gives you a refreshing boost with every sip. 

The chicken penne pasta with alfredo sauce was served beautifully. The chicken was grilled and season to perfection. It was tender, juicy and not chewy at all. The sauce was thick, filled with flavor although for me, a little too much parmesan on the top that kind of gets in your way. But overall, nice dish. 

All in all, a great place for a family lunch or dinner. Sweet and kind waiters, delivering you food within 15-20 minutes of serving time. 

For more food fun visit: instagram.com/hamzasfoodventures"

b"When the first time I visited Bait Al Malaki Mandi, it was a Thursday, restaurant was almost empty, the service and food were awesome ! First they served complimentary yakhni, then main course then we ordered tasty kunafa and then they served complimentary Qahwa with lemon and sugar.

On this visit, it was Sunday, the restaurant was busy, but still not full and there was no waiting. But still their service and food quality both declined drastically. At first, there was no yakhni, when I asked the waiter he told me that today there was a complaint in it so they were not serving it. Ok fine. But then he told me that the food will take 40 minutes as they have run out of the ready to serve madfoon. I said ok we'll wait. Then he served us the food in 20 minutes, 1 mutton madfoon was cold and dry, even the foil wrap was open. The second serving of mutton madfoon was steamy hot, full of juice, and tightly wrapped in the foil. To that, I can only make one conclusion that 1 madfoon was served straight from the kitchen and the cold one must be a returned order of some other customer(because it's foil was also open). I cant understand why they did that? They really think the customer won't feel the difference? Either they think that the customer is a fool or they don't really care about their reputation and brand image. Anyways, when I complained about it, the manager told the waiter to change that cold madfoon. After 15 minutes, he came back to tell us that it'll take allot of time to prepare fresh so we should order something else in it's place. Utterly disappointing service, if they had some problem in that why they waited 15 minutes before informing us? Anyways I told him to cancel it.
Then after the dinner, kunafa was delicious, but not as hot as it should have been. After that, he brought the bill, without asking me... Like he's wanting us to leave. Then I asked him what happened to the Qahwa... To which he replied oh it's just coming. It means he was trying to skip it too... Qahwa was served with high quantity of sugar mixed, it was sweeter than Kunafa and there was no lemon...

That was the difference in a Thursday and a Sunday, despite the fact the restaurant was still not FULL... They couldn't manage and maintain their service and food quality.

That was my last visit."

b'Subway - The forgotten place
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
\xe2\x80\xa2
I am more of a burger (andey wala burger in reality) person. Lately, something happened and I ended up at Subway. 
The branch near Maskan was not only spacious but also clean. Asked the waiter for recommendations and took some time before I indecisively and reluctantly gave my preferences. 

Steak and Cheese in Parmesan Oregnao Bread: Loved it. Flavorful minced steak (supposedly mixed with cheese!). Generous filling. Pleasant show of sauces. Soft bread. Highly recommended. 

Price  \xf0\x9f\x92\xb8 : PKR 420-ish

Rate \xe2\x9b\xa4 : 4.5/5

Peri Peri Chicken in Parmesan Oregano Bread: Mild hot. Would have preferred a bit more spice at play (given the name). The chicken pieces were well-marinated. Top it with a lot of veggies (my friend here, not me) and you might feel that the protein is a bit lost. Anyhow, fulfilling sub. 

Price \xf0\x9f\x92\xb8 : PKR 340-ish

status_message:
b'#thebitteneatRidan
\xf0\x9f\x8d\x96
For quite some time had a one eye for this place Ridan House of Mandi so I visited there yesterday for dinner with my family.
\xf0\x9f\x8d\x9a
Hmm so what we ordered \xf0\x9f\x91\x87
\xf0\x9f\x94\xb9Mutton Mandi served with complimentary  yakhni soup
\xf0\x9f\x94\xb9Kunafa
\xf0\x9f\x94\xb9Cream Caramel
\xf0\x9f\x8d\x96
We were first served with the yakhni soup it was hot and fresh good in taste but had an overpowering taste of cloves and cinnamon. 
As these spices have a very strong flavor so I would suggest them to use these spices in a small quantity so that the yakhni soup does not looses it's distinct original taste. \xf0\x9f\x8d\x9a
After the round of yakhni soup our Mandi arrived.  Oh yes I must say the quantity of that mutton was very generous! Meat was just spot on as I picked up the meat and oh man how satisfying it was to watch that perfectly slow cooked meat sliding down so beautifully off that bone\xf0\x9f\x98\x8d\xf0\x9f\x98\x8d\xf0\x9f\x98\x8b
Mutton was really good quality wise and also in taste didn't like the fresh ground pepper they sprinkled on the meat as original Mandi is not served that way. Maybe it's their variation or something.
\xf0\x9f\x8d\x96
The rice were cooked well and quantity was less than the meat however we got them refilled later. Everything was good but that extra use of garam masala was over powering everything the rice also had the same issue that I felt was ruining the originality of the actual dish, however it lacked saffron flavor as well. \xf0\x9f\x8d\x9a
Overall it was very good but just that too much use of garam masala ruined the original taste of Mandi, maybe some people like it but still it's a suggestion to cut down on the garam masala! \xf0\x9f\x8d\x96
Talking about the desserts first comes the "KUNAFA KING" double layer of vermicelli stuffed with cream cheese hardly could taste any topped with cream, it was dry there was no rosewater and sugar syrup taste in it the kunafa. Vermicelli were dry and burnt from the corners. They're doing a variation or a Desi way of kunafa I should say it's nowhere near the original kunafa. \xf0\x9f\x8d\xae
Cream caramel was a mild sweet dessert tasted like a pudding. Was a light dessert. Liked it much.
Also in the end they served us lil baby Pan's as mouth fresheners which were too cute to eat\xf0\x9f\x92\x96
\xf0\x9f\x8d\x96
A good experience just they should cut down on garam masala hopefully they'll achieve the original taste of Mandi.
For more food stories visit 
https://www.instagram.com/thebitteneat.khi/
\xf0\x9f\x8d\x9a'

b'Golden Dragon is truly God's gift to Karachi \xf0\x9f\x92\x97
Exceptional taste, unbelievably generous portions and and tremendous value for money, along with prompt service are the pillars they have built their brand on, but tonight they outdid themselves! 

We had a family dinner and my mother wasn't feeling too great so I suggested we order from GD. Now this is a woman who is known for her legendary dawats and cooking, so for her to leave it on someone else was a big deal, but since she loves GD food she agreed to go ahead with it.

We decided to order their deal for 25 people. This deal comes in 6 different options of menu and price. We ordered the deal for 12k and added soups to it.

This was our menu for the night:

Spring rolls 
White hot & sour soup
Schezuan chicken
Kung Pao fish 
Beef Chilli Dry 
Egg fried rice 
Chicken chowmein

Everything came in quantities more than sufficient for 25 people, piping jot right on time and on man the taste was fantastic. Everyone is raving about the food. 

Special shout out to Qamarunnisa Asim for her patience and help with the menu selection and Asim Mohammad Ali for ensuring everything was perfect.

I'm touched that you went to the trouble of separately preparing gluten free portions for my mother. 
People please take not that if you have gluten intolerance or MSG intolerance or any other special needs, Golden Dragon management will cater to it \xf0\x9f\x98\x8d

My mother is over the moon with the success MashaAllah and the guests have been "Goldenized" \xf0\x9f\x98\x84'

b"#TSGBloggerSMH
Moos 'n' Clucks - A casual getaway
If you're looking for an affordable quick fix for those burger and cheesy cravings then you ought to hit this eatery. 

#SMHpoints: 7.5/10

When you're with friends, seldom you opt for options that are on the fine dining side or high end side. You're in need of a quick bite at the most affordable price without damaging your taste buds. This place caters to such getaways and provides you with that casual environment to be comfortable in.

 So a couple of days back we visited this place and ordered a couple of things and here's a review of them:

#ChickenCheesePoppers: 4 Crispy chicken strips filled with creamy cheese sauce and topped with honey mustard, these beauties are a killer. On top of that considering the price, you just need to try them out! On every bite you can feel the tender chicken and the sauces blending together to give you that tantalizing sensation. 
Price: 220
Points: 4/5

#BeastFries & #CottageFries: They don't joke when they say beast. These beast fries was topped generously with minced beef, cheese and sauces. The fries were crispy, well cooked and felt amazing. The cottage fries were no far behind, blended with the cheese and served with two chicken strips filled with creamy cheese and topped with honey mustard, they're a showstopper if you're a cheese lover.
Price: 160 each
Points: 4/5

#Jalape\xc3\xb1oRoyaleBeef: Well this one didn't really appeal to my taste buds. The sauce felt a bit off with this one and was a bit too spicy and left a bad tinge. The patty however was tender and well cooked. 
Price: 260
Points: 2/5

#PortlandWinnerBeef: This is your signature beef patty burger loaded with cheese topping and creamy sauces. It feels good when you take a bite of this providing satisfaction to those cheesy creamy feeling with the tender beef blending in.
Price: 260
Points: 3/5

#GoeyBlue: A must try and a definite winner. A chicken patty filled with cheese, topped with honey mustard and delicately placed between two soft bun slices. This was a burger that was surely made with love.
Price: 280
Points: 4/5

#MacNcheeseBunlessBurger: Well this was a mixed review with out group. Being a Mac and Cheese lover, I was mesmerized by every bite of this beauty whereas the rest of us were not that impressed. As the delicately fried macaroni patties combined with a chicken patty and a mother load of cheese and honey mustard, this burger was a come back soon sign for me.
Price: 340
Points: 3.5/5

#Ambiance: Well its a pretty small place and you can feel a bit crammed if you're in a big group. It also doesn't have any restrooms which is not at all, 'okay'. They need to accommodate a restroom there.
Points: 2.5/5

#Service: Well the service is really good. The staff and management are both very courteous and the order time is also pretty efficient. Really satisfied with it.
Points: 4/5

Overall:
#Food: 8/10
#Service: 8/10
#Ambiance: 7.5/10
#Value for money: 8.5/10
#Quality: 8/10

#Total: 40/50

b'Honest review | @Chips Boat Basin
Around 2-3 month back i visited chips boat basin franchise for the 1st time and my experience was so pathetic that I decided to never visit again!
In recent days whe  one of member posted his review about chips badar, we got in lil argument and expressed my anger over brand.
I thn got an inbox from from owner of chips boat basin, he apologized and explained how all that happened and how  they have improved now and invited me over meal along with my friends. Invitation was pending from around 15 days.
We ordered
Beef american steak
Chicken Manchurian
Polo regular pizza
Beef roasted sandwich ( recommend by owner)
And ofcourse "chips"
My perception was changed instantly when fries were served in less thn 5 mins and quality was extra ordinary (as compared to my last visit where fries were having in-bowl oil party) and remaining in under 15 - 20 mins.
American beef steak : it was so perfectly cooked/grilled and tasted so well that i couldn't resist and ate it half although i dont eat beef now. Trust me u cant get better steak at this price tag from anywhere else.
Chicken Manchurian: i ordered half Chickn Manchurian and it satisfied my remaining hunger. Portion of chicken was overloaded and tatsed different (in good manner) from others.
Roasted beef sandwich: it was recommended by owner and it was next level sandwich.
Polo regular pizza: we couldn't get our hands on pizza as thr oven was malfunctioning and they were not able to serve which they were apologetic about.
Only problem i faced thr was no TV. We
 missed psl match 
Over experience 9.5
Taste 10
Ambiance 8
Sercive 10
Quality and quantity 9.5

P.s. 
This isn't paid review and neither requested by owner.
We share our experiences here so other foodies  can try new eatery 
I was a never returning customer for chips but my last experience has forced me to change mind set and visiting ver soon again.
Kudos to chips boat basin!'

b"DESI GUY!

Review for Mandi House 

It was my birthday, so my family decided to go to Mandi House after hearing so much good things about this restaurant. Places was extremely crowded with customers as it was Sunday, but they were catering everyone with proper numbering system and everything controlled by computers.

Restaurant is on the service lane of Tariq road churangi, which is not much popular but this restarant is I think standing alone at that lane. Ambiance of the is also mesmerizing, they have two options for dining, on table dine in or sitting on the floor with separate compartment. Basement area is all filled with floor sitting and ground is with table sitting area. 

Waiters and managers are well trained, their speaking skills etc was up to proper restaurant's standards. The most I like at this restaurant was cleanliness, staff was well trained to clean dirty area again and again, once the table or floor sitting is empty by customer they just get 1 or 2 minutes to get it clean and they do it perfectly.

Lets come up to the food or else people well say its paid post haha, well its not I went their about 4 times and they made me satisfied each time.

Order;

1- Mutton Yakhni 

Well it was complimentary with the food, on this visit yakhni was not up to the mark. Waiter said this is residue from the dish, if you don't like we will change that but at that moment we realize this is tasteless our food came and we left the yakhni.
My visits before this last visit, their yakhni was ok with proper mutton's taste in it will little sourness of lemon.       
rate 6/10 (Giving general rating, not based on my last visit)

2- Mutton Madfoon - (ordered for 2 persons pkr 2400/-)

Nicely marinated mutton cooked in buried style. Black pepper was over powering the whole marination and giving the acute taste of spices and mutton is self. Meat was awesomely tendered that bones can easily be separated.
rate 8/10

3- Mutton Haneeth - (ordered for 4 persons pkr 4600/-)

This dish was a bit unique for me, it was marinated with white spices specially white pepper and salt, cooker in baked style (tandoor). I personally like this as the meat was tendered pink in color and spices was balanced with salt to taste good in mouth. 
rate 9/10

Both the dishes served with rice and vegetables. Rice was properly cooked and was complimentary in quantity. Tomato sauce and raita was also served with both the dishes and they were also good to taste.

4- Kunafa - (ordered two for pkr 900/-)

Have tried kunafa in Turkey, Uae and Saudia, dish originated from Gaziantep and I always wanted to visit that place. 

Well having much idea about kunafa from all over the world, I must say this is the best Kunafa in Karachi I have ever eaten. The combination of cheesiness, sweetness and crunchiness is very soothing for mouth.
rate 9.5/10

Highly recommended place to go except sundays (rush factor).
Rating : 8/10

Sorry for not having the proper pictures as we were two hungry, I realized afterwards that I have to post it in Swot then I took pictures. 
Thanks Mandi House official for greeting so nicely for my Birthday."

b"Place: Elemento Cafe

Items ordered: 
-Moskava Fried Chicken 
-Chicken Tarragon 
-Pina Colada
-Chocolate Milkshake 

Review: 

Moskava Fried Chicken: 
It was deep fried chicken with a filling of creamy cheese sauce and mushrooms, topped with special sauce. It was served with mashed potatoes and veggies. The chicken itself was crispy from outside and tender from inside.
Rating: 8/10

Chicken Tarragon: 
Chicken Tarragon was tender, it was cooked to perfection with mild spices. It was served with mashed potatoes and veggies. There was a deal, too. (2 chicken tarragon and 2 drinks, only for Rs. 999/-) 
Rating: 9/10

Pina Colada: 
It was refreshing. I had an authentic pina colada after ages, tbh! 
Rating: 9.5/10

Chocolate Milkshake:
It was average, though it wasn't bad. But it should've been thicker when it comes to consistency. 
Rating: 6/10

Elemento Cafe is located at Tariq road. The ambiance overall is good. You can have a meal for Rs. 500-600 per head with a decent amount of portion size."

b"DESI GUY!
Review for Meat the Cheese

After hearing so much positive and negative comments from my social circle, I decided to give it a try to this restaurant for having hype for cheese.
My visit to Meat the Cheese was quick though, as I was craving for meaty food.
Ambiance 9/10

1- Tenderloin Steak 

First of all, it was the first restaurant in my list where I got the steak in around 10mins. My temperature was medium well as usual, and their steak happened to be among the best steak in Karachi. 
Tenderloin's size was good and it was very juicy & tender, middle part was the perfect pink according to the steak standards. If we talk about presentation, it was brilliantly played with the potatoes, vegetables, mushrooms and sauces. Their were two sauces in the plate, one was quite peppery and other was creamy, both the sauces was amazing in taste with the meat.
9/10

2- Jalapeno Pizza 

This was the perfect plat bread pizza with ample topping on it wit chicken and veges. I have tried pizzas in Italy, can say this was the similar version to that pizza. 
Overall taste was good, just suggestion from my side to try to make it round in size.
8/10

My visit to this restaurant wasn't planned, as I was going to other restaurant that was closed and then I came to MTC.
My overall experience to MTC was really good and I do recommend this restaurant in my social circle also...
Overall ratings 9/10

Note: Team of Meat the Cheese please find the way for eliminating the nasty smell when heated raclette come on the floor.

Total Damage: 2,588, including drinks and 13 % tax."

status_message: b"Me and my wife recently went to Vintage - OTG at LuckyOne Mall. We ordered Nachos, Crispy Chicken Wrap and Cheesy Chicken Tortilla Sandwiches along with French Fries. The order was delivered on time which was the only good thing about the outlet. It might used to be a good food outlet as we read a lot of good reviews here but it was a bad choice. The Nachos that were served didn't contain anything but Chips (Soggy and not fresh) and cheese. I have had Nachos at many places and this was nothing like Nachos at all. I had to took them back after a couple of picks. The Crispy Chicken Wrap was not at all Crispy and you can call it Messy Chicken Wrap because the Tortilla was burnt and you could taste the burn throughout and the Tortilla was all messed up with the sauce and I couldn't hold it at all. Everytime I took a bite messed up my face which was embarassing. The Cheesy Chicken Tortillas consisted of burnt Tortillas as well and it didn't taste good at all due to the burn. Turns out it was a complete let down. I won't be taking a chance with this outlet again. Thanks for ruining the evening :)"

b"DESI GUY! 

Review for The SugarCane Bar 

Personally know about this brand, this brand got popularity from Karachi Eat Food Festival, as participated in KEFF's two installments 2017 and 2018. 

Just a few days back they opened up their outlet at chota bukhari near Afghanish. Their products are also available at Afghanish. 

Sorry guys ai don't have pictures for what I have tried from their menu. 

1- SugarCane Milkshake pkr 270

Tried this thing for the first time, and milk combination with sugarcane juice was just awesome. 
9/10

2- Cococane pkr 280

This is the unique thing, I have ever tried. The perfect blend of coconut milk, sugarcane juice and their secret procedure. Taste was very smooth and sweet though. 
9.5/10

3- Pan Mint pkr 170

Out of pan's flavour, they are using real pan and mint blend with sugarcane juice. Very strong pan and minty taste sweetened with pure sugarcane juice. 
8/10

Overall I like the Cococane the most in their menu cause of its uniqueness but other items are also good as they are pure sugarcane juices with sugarcane ice and making in hygienic and clean environment. 
Rating: 9/10"

b"I seldom write good reviews on Swot because I just prefer to do the bad ones. It's more fun plus it's simply an action of absolute passionate disdain. However in the case of Golden Bite Pizza I'll have to say i'm blown away. Golden Bite Pizza interior looks like a typical restaurant inside a small shop. Their Kitchen was open so we can see the cleaness. but Overall i was not impressed with the decor and ambiance. The food is what i'm most impressed with (after all I was not there to smell the roses)

We Order 3 Different flavours of Pizza. 
1) GoldenBite Special
2) Kabab Chaska 
3) Fajita Sensation 

The Kabab chaska was simply amazing. I'd chose this flavour on any other flavour in Karachi, It was really outstanding.  
Fajita Sensation was Average. It was not that Spicy as i thought before ordering. ( I like a bit Spicy though).
And last but not least Golden Bite Special. It was also really good, morelike Chicken Supreme Pizza but with a little touch of Creamy Tikka Pizza.

Final thoughts:

Ambiance 6/10
Food 8.5/10
service 9/10 (it was quick)
Value of money 8/10

I'd definately like to visit there again with my office buds. & hope to enjoy variaty of pizza once again."

b'I visited Westeros yesterday, an open dhaaba. I tried the best seller Jalape\xc3\xb1o pizza first, it was a brick oven baked thin crust pizza. The flavor was on point, juicy smoked chicken pieces and the cheese. Moving on to Souvlaki, Greek wrap,  that won my heart with a great tzatziki sauce and the crunch of fresh veggies and well seasoned chicken. Food was better than what we usually get to eat at other dhabbas.
Last of all, for the sweet tooth, I had the most delicious fire chocolate brownie served fresh and hot on sizzlinng platter with a generous scoop of my favorite vanilla ice cream. I seriously love chocolate too much, so, I loved every single bite of it. Unfortunately I did not take a picture of that delicious brownie. 

Price breakdown:
Jalape\xc3\xb1o pizza: 550rs
Souvlaki: 300rs
Fire chocolate brownie:360rs
Rating: 9/10'

b"#TSGBLOGGERTEHNIAT

Eatery: Xander's

Heading over to Xanders for lunch last Friday was one of the best decisions I've so far made this year. Friend was in the mood for Alfredo pasta while I wanted soup because of my sore throat. It's another story though that I ended up ordering Parmesan Crusted Chicken instead. Just couldn't resist! \xf0\x9f\x98\x8b

Parmesan Crusted Chicken was one of the best one's I've had. The chicken was crispy, juicy and flavorsome. The mushroom sauce very well complimented the chicken as it was light, not too runny or thick. Mashed potatoes which came as a side were perfect too!

Both of us loved the Alfredo Pasta too. The perfect white sauce and grilled chicken satiated our pasta cravings. 

The place was a bit noisy as it was packed and school children were around but the service was prompt. 

Xanders totally won us over! 

Taste: 4/5
Quality: 4/5
Quantity: 4/5
Price: 4/5
Presentation: 4/5

Overall experience: 8/10"

For our parent's 27th anniversary we went to Sultan- The Royal Eatery and weren't disappointed \xf0\x9f\xa4\xb7\xf0\x9f\x8f\xbb\xe2\x80\x8d\xe2\x99\x80\xef\xb8\x8f

The main course had alfredo pasta which was tasty beyond words, italian mushroom steak which I didn't like as much but is a good choice for people who don't love a lot of spices, daal makhni which was every desi food lover's dream daal\xf0\x9f\x98\x81\xe2\x9d\xa4\xef\xb8\x8f and last but not least mutton karahi which sizzled every taste bud\xf0\x9f\x94\xa5
For the drinks we got Blue Lagoon, Raspberry Colada and Mint Lemonade which we're absolutely amazing \xf0\x9f\x92\x97
As for the dessert we had Creme Brulee which wasn't what we expected as it had a distinct egg smell but overall we had an amazing experience \xe2\x9c\xa8\xe2\x9d\xa4\xef\xb8\x8f

b"Got burger + fries from Buntburger Bunt burgers.
This deal comprises a burger with a serving of fries. 
The burger I got is called Pompous. It had smashed double beef patties topped with cheddar cheese, bell peppers, tomato, bits of onions with lettuce, mayo and the special BUN-T sauce.
Super delicious. I couldn't even tell that it had beef patties! The sauce was really good, normally I take the vegs out of a burger, but not this one because all the flavours complemented each other. What I specially liked was how the patties were soft and juicy but not undercooked, they were also not dry or overcooked either. Perfectly cooked \xf0\x9f\x8d\x94
The fries were thin and crisp, just the way I prefer them. However, they could do with a little more salt. 

Rs 399/- alone for the burger"

b'I didn't believe my friends when they stated this was an ideal Iranian restaurant in k-town. A friend and I made our journey down this gem of a restaurant and we were pleasantly surprised, but there were a few significant differences.

The menu rarely collapses into purple prose apart from the occasional "palate-awakening" and the "Show Time" section of dishes but #ChupaRustom does offer dishes I've never heard of before. Take "Machroon key Sughaat" as an example. A beautiful balance of sweetness and acidity in a traditional tomato rasam, poured over a seafood festival with tomato bread on the side. 

The first, Garlic Tikkah an amalgam of boneless chicken perfumed with the heady flavor of garlic tikkah spices, was punctuated with roasted garlic and paneer. Darjan Darjan Kebab, fantastic juicy seekh kebabs bursting with flavors of fresh onions, herbs and green chillies

A mexican selections with two splendid flavors arrived with a mountain of greens. Desi Tacos. Soft makai ki Roti, sarson ka saag, Paneer and Desi salsa on one side and braised chicken tikkah lacha on the other. This was very recommended, however it didn't really come up to the mark. 

Prawn curry is a creamy, velvety dish with delicious depth of flavour. Less unusual, though no less authentic, was the rich, filling curry leaves, with its slowly simmered chunks of prawns in a vibrantly seasoned rai and tomato sauce.

Lastly for dessert, we ordered both that were on the menu. Doodh doubleroti which is apparently inhouse pound cake, seared and soaked in almond milk, topped with crispy jalebi and clotted cream (I searched and searched and searched but did not find my jalebi). Shahi turkre. Freshly baked bread stuffed with khoya. Golden, deep fried and topped off with sweet milk, almond and pistachios (nope.) 

We were also served with strawberries dipped in dark chocolate complimentary. Strawberries were incredibly fresh. 

Although Chupa Rustom's menu narrowly focuses on desi specialties, its not a desi restaurant. However, their quality, presentation and service is unbeatable. 

WITHOUT THE SLIGHTEST SHADOW OF DOUBT THEIR KEBABS REMAINS THE BEST. 

(Things that took incredibly long: wheat naan + our remaining cash from the bill.)'

b'Rant! Horrible experience at Loco! Just got back home and boy let me roll up my sleeves for this huge rant I never usually write.
Talk about getting a Grand Birthday being reserved at this fairly new 'Supposed' edgy ' Spanish 'eatery in Karachi being Utterly spoiled and ruined by None other than the Loco staff and the ALMOST- CHOKING- TO-DEATH ( WITHOUT A HAZARD AHEAD FOOD WARNING SIGN) Food.
Have money to waste?No?Good, Because every penny you've earned is precious. Oh So you have money to waste? Head out to Loco ;) 
Let's talk about the food shall we? 
On a table of 12, Just 3 Menu cards were distributed which had to be awkwardly rolled and shared out because Apparently they were short on them. How embarrassing!
Okay - The FOOD and The person taking our order. 
Being a tiny cosy place, with music too loud for the person to even take out orders it was a Mayhem. With only 2 servers actually serving the entire Lot at Loco, I feel sorry! For you and the customers.
FOOD - Here we come. 
Upon arriving we were instantly told 'WE ARE NOT SERVING PIZZA's and ANY GRILLED CHICKEN'. Woah! That was a major shocker! On such a limited menu you have the nerve to slap our appetites, knowing we've reserved prior to the day AND ITS A BIRTHDAY DINNER, NOT A BLOODY WALK-IN CASUAL DINNER FOR 2.
Okay, so 6 of us who wanted Pollo Al Carbon(Grilled Chicken) and Pizza went like Fine, what other good option do you have. To this they were least bothered to tell us any other good option so we went for Ajillo Chicken dish. Talk about Chicken swimming in a broth of Bitter chilli oil enough to choke you to death by the first inhale. Oh, USA might invade the single  serving thinking the oil is a Jackpot from the Middleeast! With three tiny rubber breads, it was sheer Punishment. The other Beef entree was another nail in the coffin. Too chewy, too bitter to swallow. AND A FEW WERE NOT EVEN SERVED TILL WE ALMOST BEGGED THEM THAT WE'RE ABOUT TO LEAVE PLEASE SERVE.
