b'I wanted to avail these vouchers of Naanwich from Chachajees and Kashmir Day voucher from COOLfies. 

Chachajees had conducted this contest to snap a picture of their naanwhich advertisement and inbox for their page. I saw this in Dolmen City Mall's magazine which I had subscribed so took a photo and sent them . Got my voucher on January 30, 2018 which I had to us before 28th February. I availed it at Tariq Road branch without difficulties and got my three naanwhiches for 520 rs . One is for 260 rs. The taste was good and it was difficult to eat it with ettiquettes...

Now COOLfies whose screenshot I have in mobile , but my fingers are typing from a laptop keyboard hence I cant show the evidence that I was one of the winners of Kashmir Day contest with few other people. The message I got clearly said it was again buy one and get one free and I could avail it as many times til 28th February. I showed the message to the guy at the stall of COOLfies and he was scared like I am asking to give all kulfi's for free.
" Yeh offer 18 feb tak thi abhi ka humko nai pata" . I said to text the person infront of me , he did " type" a few words on his mobile, but since I was standing I did want to try it. Hence I ordered one Crunchy Crunch regular for 160 rs. I repeated my voucher multiple times but he was not bothered nor the response ever came on his mobile. The kulfi was just fine and vermicelli was old for sure since it was rubbery as if the guy just wanted to get rid off it. COOLfies if you cant afford to give through competitions why do you even announce such things? 
This was a very good lesson for me that never go for so called buy one get one free, its better to eat on your money only instead of expecting you to stay on your words. When the message clearly stated its 28th February you changed the date to  18th February and if you did so could have atleast informed me . Never going to have kulfies from you nor I want anything complimentary . Tumko tumhari kulfi mubarak!'

b"In a city of 22 million people food places that cater to the entire family are always welcome. Pan Asian cuisine is one that appeals to a lot of desi palates. The tangy & hot, sweet & sour - lip pukering at times are the flavors you expect when you enter such a place. When we go with a large group we also want the quantities to be adequate.

One such place has nearly completed a year in the city and the SWOT team lead by Hina Ilyas made their way to analysis. as always the individual reviews will be posted at comments here are a few candid pictures clicked by the team.

The overall #swotanalysis and grading resulted in a 70% or 3.5\xe2\xad\x90

Bonsai Pan Asian Kitchen is a well located restaurant , easily found via google maps (since its on the intersection of two major khayabans in phase 6, with ample parking and valet service. The interior is charming and minimalist which is very modern PanAsian. comfortable seating and bright cheerful staff to greet you.

Menu selection boasts of Japanese, Thai, Chinese and Korean dishes. Hence something everyone in a group can enjoy. The quantities are large and the quality of the meats used excellent and the flavors cater well to the desi palate. As in spicy tangy sweet and sour.

Another thing we were pleased to note was that they are experimenting and trying out different seasonings and tastes so future visits are definitely in the picture to try those out once on the menu

A couple of minor issues - 
1} that while the staff is very accommodating and attentive they are very slow - the time between order taking to food on the table - is about 20 mins, 
2} no hot beverage especially green tea - which is a must at a Pan Asian.

Overall a positive addition to the Karachi Food scene. Team The SWOT's GUIDE wishes them all the best for the future and urges the #SWOTTIES to try this place out."

b'Review; #Biryani  Haji vs Madni vs Mazaidaar

Being a Die hard Biryani fan, the hunt for the best option in kcity shall never end though, but these three have been the ones suggested and raved about, so decided to hold a triple threat match among these..

Bought all three with a request for extra spicy, an allooo and fresh.. Madni located near Sher Shah Suri Road, Mazaidar a ten mnts drive to Madni and  last but not least Haji Biryani at Jamshed Road.

For me quanity doesnt matter, tbh the right amount of spice, rice Quality (Not sela please) and  just the ideal steamed prepared Biryani is what matters most. So I m not suggesting anybody to opt for these but this is what I observed..

Madni Biryani; strong aromatic, right amount of chicken and rice Quality was decent but lacked ideal spice level for my liking 240 pkr for double.

Haji Biryani; perfect rice, absolute perfect steam, aromatic but not as strong as Madni but spice level rocked and fresh 170 pkr for double.

Mazaidar Biryani; lacked steam, decent amount of chicken/allooo, lacked any spices at all.. not happy with rice at all.. 130pkr single plate..

The pictures below have been taken at same time, venue and camera.. 

P.s I have tried Haji and Madni around multiple times before giving the final verdict and Haji is all rounder for me atm. Cheers!'

b"Went to Copacabana Churascarria last week. Brilliant food, very authentic. The buffet is made up of a 7 course served at the table on a skewer style buffet. 

The lamb and the tenderloin were to die for but there was some fatty umami like beef cut (something starting with a P) that was just simply beautiful (picture below)

Great atmosphere.. Great service... good value for money as they comped my youngest sons meal and he ate for free.. they were even nice enough to parcel what was left on our plates for home making this a one of a kind buffet.

2 adults and 2 kids ate to our hearts content for around PKR. 3600 with bottomless mint lemonade or soft drinks. 

This amount didnt include the extra 700 bucks that i shelled out on the Cairpirinhia which was probably the most delicious non alcoholic drink I've had in ages

Areas to improve.. maybe ditch the chicken wings and focus on the beef and lamb or perhaps accord the customer the option to choose"

b'"Karachi guy"
 
The pizza fries from bite 4 delight are they worth it ??? 

After seeing numerous reviews on Pizza fries from bites for delight it made me anxious.  I always give one chance to new outlets to impress me or It would be my first and the last visit . we went there at around 7 o'clock and luckily the queue was not too long or not too short (jo thi  uska  koi  saar  paow  nai tha) . the first thing that came into my mind when i tried to order was bhai yeh sirf fries hai tu Itni zillat  Kyun because there was no system sab log chips wale Chacha kay moo main ghus Huye thy so as a pound Pakistani I did the same. As the first batch of fries  came which made around 20 boxes the Chacha took money from the 20 people standing there and then we had to wait for 5 minutes because the fries had to go into the microwave so the cheese could melt. After 30 min or so I got my order and for those 30 min I was just thinking wtf  am I doing Itni Kuwari for fries. Finally my order was ready and i took it to my car and opened the box. YES the taste was superb and it made me forget all the misery. The price of one box is 160rs which is very economical for the quantity and the quality being served
So I give it a 9/10 for the taste 
P.s the flavours made my day although the experience of waiting there was not good khair akhir me Sabar ka phal bara cheesy hota hai :D'

b'Chupa Rustam. Went back after a month for dinner and had a enjoyable experience.  We got very good service courtesy Ernest, who was serving us. 
We sat out on the patio and enjoyed the karachi breeze. 
For starters, ordered the daal soup( punch something) which was actually delicious.  Similar to mauligawtany. My friend ordered bengan ( open faced Eggplant) with roti and yogurt. He really liked it and wiped it off.
I had the mutton chops on a bed of mushroom rice with pickled onion.  The chops were cooked to perfection. Not for all palettes. 
Very different flavour and I enjoyed experimenting.
For dessert we ordered Gajar ka halwa which was rich with different nuts and not heavy. We drowned our food with Kahva and gurr.  Total bill 3k.'

b"Went to Desi Gali on Bukhari for dinner tonight. 6 of us went around 8:00 p.m. and we were quite excited when we saw the menu. Flying saucer, dum qeema, masala bites, shawarma and guess what? Nothing was available except parathas and bunkababs. 

Khair, because we were starving at that point and primarily ventured out for bunkababs, that's what we ordered, along with anda paratha (Not pictured), aalu paratha (Pictured), and lachaydaar paratha (Not pictured). 

Thankfully whatever we ordered more than made up for the non-availability of other items we wanted to try. The Special anda daal bunkabab was almost as good as my childhood favorite, Super Nursery Bunkabab. The lachayddar paratha was truly lachaydaar, buttery and crispy, delightful bites of goodness. The anda paratha was reminiscent of old-school dhaaba style paratha, where the omelet is sandwiched on top of the paratha, making it a greasily delightful mouthful. Don't try to soak up the excess oil with a tissue. Just don't. Enjoy the greasy goodness. The aalu paratha was a spicy surprise, with a generous potato filling within the crispy confines of the paratha itself. 3 cups of doodh patti minus ilaichi were ordered and enjoyed as well. 

Desi Gali is definitely worth a visit, as long as you're willing to compromise on not having half the menu available.

P.S: There is an adorable stray cat at Desi Gali, marmalade coat. If you see him, please be nice to him. He seems mostly tame and is willing to eat anything thrown his way. He's a playful, innocent creature. Ignore him if you don't like cats, don't throw things at him or shoo him away."

b'I'm a regular customer of Kababjees and this review is to bring it to their management's attention that how their Johar Branch is going to take out the loyal customers from them. So I visited Kabajees - Gulistan.e.Jauhar branch on Friday and was being forced to have their stinky fish!! Oh and My review on this is going to be very long and whiny.

Upon ordering their famous Fish n Chips, we were being served with some very stinky fish. When we complained, they (waiter and manager) started arguing with us on how the fish is not at all stinky and we shall have this one and try it again. "UFFF ITNI OBVIOUS BAD BOU THI US MAI, TRY AGAIN KA SUN K BHOOSA MAARNE KA DIL KARA"
Anyways we asked them to take it away. They then forced us that they'll bring another one which doesn't stink.. Well after waiting for half an hour, we told them to cancel the order and bring the bill since it's taking way too long. b"Place - Mcdonalds App

So an extra ordinary marketing effort from McDonald's launch of loaded fries prompted all of us ReShape Hospitality to download the app and order the Fries in not one, two but three flavors :-). Little did we know that we were in for disappointment equal to 3 times as we went through each flavor. A very ordinary launch by McDonalds. The fries were not the classic skinny ones but quite thick and soggy, sauces were nothing special but they were anything but loaded. They were supplemented by a strange Chaat Masala like Lemon Chilli Masala which they have imported from India. Nothing Special. Each flavor was north of RS. 200. 

1- BBQ Fries - We will let the pic help you judge for yourself.

2- Nacho Cheese Fries - The sauce was decent in this one or maybe just because it was Cheese but quite ordinary over all. Maybe adding Jalape\xc3\xb1os would have helped but we didn't add them on. 

3- Mayo Garlic Fries - So many eateries have perfected the art of Garlic Mayo in Karachi, even some Roll Points have better Garlic Mayo products.

Pakistan in general is a very small community for food eateries where things go viral and trends are very short lived but very helpful for brands that can capitalize. McDonalds fails despite being a truly global brand. Will I not stop for a McOreo late at night because of this mishap no, but as soon as I have a better local option for the flurry, Ill run. Beware :-)

#RFA #ReShapeHospitality #NotLoadedFries #ReshapeFA"

b'#TSGBLOGGERHAMZA  

Eatery: The Deli

This post contains TWO of Deli's highlights: one is their catering service and the 
second is their high tea.

So, The Deli has a reputation for being a fine, semi-formal, kind of dining place ever since it opened. The setting, the d\xc3\xa9cor, the fancy menu items and much more. So far, it has lived up o its reputation when it comes to their ala carte menu. I found very few people who have complained about horrible experiences there, true nothing is ever perfect but the deli has hit their high notes well. 

The first few pictures that depict food being setup on a separate table shows how they provide customization catering services for parties, whether at the deli or anywhere else you'd wish. They estimate that this beautifully setup with a buffet costs around PKR 2000 per head, and go more depending on how you want to customize it to your needs. For more information, you can get in touch with The Deli management themselves. This is something we did not taste. But what we did try was their high tea. 

This is what their menu was for a regular high tea: 

Vietnamese rice wrapper rolls
The deli classic taco (replaced with mango salsa and tortilla)
Tartine with cherry tomato and basil
Tartine with seared beef and horseradish 
Classic chicken Ceaser's wrap 
Wood fire oven pizzetta 
Buttermilk scones with strawberry jam and clotted cream 
Chocolate plum tart 
Mango Eton mess 
Tea/coffee

The timings for high tea are from 4pm to 6pm daily and their introductory prices are 750 + tax per head. For those looking for ratings, find them right below \xe2\x80\x93 others looking for a detailed review please read further: 

Taste: 7.5/10
Presentation: 8.5/10
Variety: 8/10
Quality and quantity (for 2 people): 8/10
Value for money: Yes
Location: 8/10

Because it's a fancy dining place so for me, the variety and presentation seemed more significant than the taste of the food itself. As a food blogger, all aspects are covered though. For me the fact that they presented us with a nice range of palate varying small servings \xe2\x80\x93 enough to fill two people with one platter, was applaudable. They take their sweet time setting up your table, but once they get it ready and bring in the servings, you kind of go nuts digging in. There was enough of everything for everybody.

The serving was generous, the presentation was eye catching and food tasted pretty good on its own. Its not your regular high tea, it's very "English." Which is interesting to me, because it seemed they pulled it off quite well. They have a new barista which in turn now serves you great coffee. I think my caf\xc3\xa9 mocha was something I find consistently good at such places. 

A few things that stood out for me were \xe2\x80\x93 the tartine with seared beef and horseradish, chocolate plum tart, mango eton mess and the Vietnamese rice paper rolls. The beef was seared medium and had a nice perfect pink right in the center \xe2\x80\x93 which for me is absolutely stunning. The tartine itself was a sort of garlic bread with seared beef on top of it and served with horseradish (which ironically is a very common English dressing used to dress beef, famously in the UK \xe2\x80\x93 surprise surprise at my English reference?) this was actually interesting because it is something niche in the market and the foodies of Karachi deserve diversity in their palate, and it makes me happy to see that there are restaurants trying to put up a good show for everyone. 

Anyway, the chocolate plum tart was just off the charts. The crust was crispy, and the tart itself had that perfect balance between the tanginess of the plum and the sweetness of chocolate and it just gave a nice, romantic gesture to your taste buds. 

The mango eton mess is also, an English dessert served in a small cup and was a mixture of broken meringue, whipped cream, tart crumble and mango slices. It was also covered with a little caramel syrup in the end. It was like a little sweet haven in my mouth when I had this. An absolute delicacy. 

The Vietnamese rice paper roll isn't as easy to pull off as well as they managed to, so hats off to them for creating an overall very delicate, yet amazing high tea experience. 

For those who are looking for a nice place to formally have a high tea, I'd 
recommend The Deli.

#TheDeliKarachi #TheDeli #HiTea'

status_message:
b"Pizza 363 (opposite Rabiya City)

So I went with friends for a quick meal to Pizza 363 that I had read about on swots. And what an experience we had! I'll easily call it the best pizza joint in town. 
-The AC was not working at all and we just sat there sweating away, which was great considering the amount of calories we were going to devour on this cheat day. I had no idea they provided complimentary sauna services too. Thumbs up for that. 
-The place ran completely on self service. We had to even get the cutlery and food ourselves from the counter. Again, the exercise was good for us.
-We ordered just 1 large pizza (flavour: hot & cold) initially because we wanted to try it first and then order more. And they took only around 40 minutes to prepare it. Have you ever seen a faster service than this? I bet not. 
-Coming to the pizza, the quantity was great. But then I think the restaurant was adamant at not letting us ruin our diet so they made sure to serve us a pizza we are unable to eat. Three grown up guys, who can easily finish 2 large pizzas, ended up with three slices still left of the only 1 large we ordered. In fact, looking around we could see that others also were unable to eat their pizzas. (Or maybe I was just seeing things, after all I was sweating badly and got dehydrated).

b"#TSGBloggerSMH
Delfrio Smchs: Poor customer service, untrained staff, and average food.

#SMHpoints: 1/20

This was the second bad experience with this eatery and itts totally off the list now. The previous experience was at brunch but that was excusable, that review will also be posted soon but today was completely unacceptable and disrespectful.

Here's a recap of the situation:
We went there for drinks this morning and had decided our order which was mint lemonades. We asked the waiter to take our order thrice and all three times he asked us to wait and that he'll be right back. 20 minutes passed and after waving the manager our order was finally placed and we redeemed our bogo as well. We were patiently waiting for our order for 15 minutes and after that the same server to whom we asked to take our order earlier came to ask if the order was placed. We waited another 20minutes between which we had waved the manager twice and no response was received. Finally, we got up and to leave when the server who took our order asked us what happened I told him the situation and instead of accepting his fault he just went to the counter and plainly cancelled the order without any guilt or apology. 

Del Frio trust me your food isn't out class or above average yet I have put up with you in the past but this attitude of today and your overall customer service is pathetic. Never again am I or my team visiting this eatery where the servers aren't trained properly and 50minutes are not enough for you to make simple mint lemonades.
No matter how good the food of an eatery is, if the customer service isn't good, nothing is good.

#Ambiance: Well, the seating arrangement isn't that good and the tables aren't even clean and are  close to the dirty walls. 

#CustomerService: 0/10
#Ambiance: 1/10

#Total: 1/20"

status_message: b"McDonald's! 'That's not you' was a surprise reaction yesterday when i tried their newly launched series of loaded fires. Thought it would be the same lazy long making that famous (M) curve ones which are their standard fries but shocked to see some thick fat, (overall completely different potatos) that spoiled my party. After enquiring with the management, i was told its imported from India. Well since pak importing potatoes n veggies from their or lekson group which owns McD here might have done on their private terms but question i asked first on their official page before sharing here, How can an International brand who has world most unique, demanded, consumed fries would ever sale completely different style of fries which they are not associated with over the decades? How can this be possible? Where else in the world this happening? Isn't it some kind of transition to replace original slim fires with these fat ones in the future? Hopefully not. Furthermore, when i checked the box it's written 'printed in Pakistan' wow! what an information! For edible/eateries n stuff , it's not important where their boxes are printed, rather some more worthy information for example a product of or / imported from india if that's the case. Please do not sale someone else's potatos inside the World's Best Fries Place. <\\3"

status_message:
b'Tried Junaidi's Pizzeria today, and must I say, it's a little hidden gem in this sprawling metropolis. I don't know when this place was established, but I'm glad I found it when I did. 

It's not very avidly marketed on Facebook, and I think it's a really rightly run unit. Ordered the split between Pepperoni and Chicken, with extra cheese and meat. 

Delivery was timely, and the pizza itself was much bigger than I thought. Definitely above 16". It's a thin crust, no-frills pizza that tastes really good. 

It's a pizza that doesn't want to stand out; it wants to blend in. There are no stuffings of useless ingredients, or darkened crusts. It doesn't want to make a big deal of itself. It knows it'd going to go in your mouth, and accepts its destiny.

The new concept if pay per slice is definitely a good one, and maybe it'll catch on in this big city. 

I am really glad to see that this place is getting traction, and I hope it becomes that classic neighborhood pizza parlor of the modern age.'

Foodpanda returns with Vol 2 of Bites n Vibes, this time at the other end of the city! The event is being held at Pavilion End Club, in Gulshan, and I must commend them for organizing something here.

Arabi

b"After severe procrastinating, here I am with my first ever review on SWOT.
On the suggestion  of fellow Swotties, Rao Danish, Zeeshan Haqq, and Waqas Ahmed Khan, I visited Elemento Caff\xc3\xa8 with my better half anticipating a good foodilicious experience...
And we did get it... The moment we enter the place, we smiled, excited about the beautiful decor the place has. Lovely dim lights, energetic yet not-loud-at-all music, and comfortable, luxurious seats.
The service was amazing and down to earth. Order was received in decent time and the presentation of the platter was really salivating...

So Swotties, feel free to go there and enjoy the deal (2 tarragon chicken with 2 drinks in 999) and perhaps some more... You won't regret it for sure...

b'So we went to Yadgar Fish last week and all of us were trying it for the first time. We were five people and ordered four different dishes being
. Fish karahi
. Prawn masala rice 
. Surmai fry
. Rahu fry

The quantity is served in measure of pao which meant that each dish would be one or two serves. Winner of the night was Fish karahi and I would recommend everyone to try it out.
Prawn masala rice was the second best dish and the full plate was heaped with rice and prawns. 
Both fried fish were tender, juicy and good in taste too. 

The five of us shared the food and since their was chappati and rice, the entire meal was very filling. The ambiance of this place is not very well since it is a very old restaurant but the food  is very, very delicious. 

The bill we received was a surprise because we were not expecting anything less than  Rs 2000; not to mention that the prices of fish were not mentioned in the menu as they keep fluctuating according to the season.'

b"Appreciation post time! As a faithful member of the Pizza cult in Karachi I write this post with a feeling of triumph at having been treated to simply one of the best Pizza's I have had the fortune of gracing my taste buds. In what can be said as a case of serendipity I stumbled upon, Junaidi's Pizzeria.
Located in an inconspicuous street in Badar Commercial is this little shop run by Sohaib Junaidi, a Pizza enthusiast inspired by the $1 slice theme prevalent in New York. For those of you who don't know about the concept, it is quite self explanatory, in that, they sell individual slices for about a dollars equivalent in rupees so its easy on the wallet but ALSO you can even sponsor a slice for a complete stranger by simply paying ahead for a slice and pasting a post-it on the wall with your message and name on it which anyone can come and claim to get a free slice; something the owner feels is a way to create a sense of community, happiness and ofcourse a satisfied tummy.
Coming to the quality of the Pizza itself, the all-important dough was baked to near perfection with just the right amount of crisp and charred texture. The homemade sauce was also spot on, complemented by a fresh layer of cheese and a fairly accurate three way ratio between the toppings, the cheese and the sauce. 
I urge everyone who has even an inkling of fondness for Pizza to treat themselves to JUNAIDI'S, appreciate its concept, and hopefully in the process, revive a waning Pizza culture in Karachi."

b'#TSGBLOGGERHAMZA

Eatery: Mocca 

Verdict: You can't ever get over their bright white and light, wooden brown interior. With great coffee and good food, it's becoming like a second home. 

Overall Rating: 8/10

Mocca has exponentially expanded their restaurant empire. From Karachi, Lahore and Islamabad with at least a couple of outlets in every city \xe2\x80\x93 this one is the main hub in Karachi, the one on main Khayaban e Shahbaz. This place is now hard to miss and has become home for all coffee lovers in the city. And what could be better than having a great cup of coffee with good food coupled with it?

They have recently opened their "Mocca Lounge" in their basement which elevates their already plush interior and brings real life to eatery. And so, my friend and I had to go check it out. 

I ordered the Pulled BBQ Beef for my main course, Kiwi and mint lemonade and a Swiss Choc Brownie topped with a Swiss Choc Ganache and a scoop of gelato along with some macaroons for dessert. 

Average price per head: Less than PKR 1400/- plus tax

Overall ratings: 
Taste: 8.5/10
Quality: 8/10
Quantity: 8.5/10
Presentation: 8/10
Ambiance: 9/10
Service: 9/10
Location: 9/10

Among many things, service for the restaurant is critical. To my liking the food was served within 15 minutes of the order and although missing the warmth of the plates, the food itself was warm and comforting. The Pulled BBQ Beef is finely shredded slow roasted beef, stuffed in a grilled flatbread with melted cheddar cheese and great balance of spiciness from the BBQ flavor \xe2\x80\x93 served with a hummus and a lettuce, rocket leaves and sun-dried tomato slaw to just sort of balance the acidity from the meat.
 
It has tremendous flavor and is a good filling for a growling stomach. You just pick the sandwich up and dip it in the hummus and munch on \xe2\x80\x93 because there's just no stopping you then. 

The Kiwi mint lemonade served to be a great tool for digestion, it was a light and refreshing cocktail to go with something so overwhelming as a dish. 

At the end of it all, the most amazing way you can end your dinner is with the Swiss Chocolate brownie, smothered in a melted Swiss Chocolate Ganache served with a homemade scoop of vanilla gelato. It was just rich, creamy, and beats any chocolate lava cake on any day because it doesn't bring you down or overpower you into making you feel lazy.

And last but not the least, the lovely macaroons. Packed with sugary flavor, the chocolate hazelnut and sea salt caramel macaroon (if you're not too much into chocolate) just really helps you run through towards the finishing line of dinner. Amazing. 

Great coffee, good comfort food and a string of amazing desserts with the best possible ambiance anywhere in the city.

For more food goodies, follow: www.instagram.com/hamzasfoodventures'

I ordered a med pizza from the midnight deals section at 11:15 pm and was told that it'll be delivered within 45 minutes, it was still a little shocking considering the fact that I live within a walking distance from one of their branches ( due to some reason I couldn't get it myself ).

b'Tonight owing to sudden hunger pangs , decided to go out for dinner. After much delibration , all-time favorite Hot n Spicy Khadda Market branch was selected. Had been a regular customer at their restaurant for quite some years.

Precisely, ordered 2 crispy broast with garlic mayo dip and steamed rice, however the waiter suggested or rather insisted to try Afghani Pulao. On his 'recommendation' ordered Afghani Pulao ."The Comedy of Errors" started as the food  arrived.

The fries accompanying the broast were totally cold as was the small piece. When I told the waiter , he suggested to deep fry those same fries and piece again ,however on insistence those things were replaced after a good 8 to 10 minutes.  In the meanwhile, the waiter dropped in the middle to inform " sir fries complimentary nh hn apko pay krna parega" . I told him to take those on my plate and replace the same with fresh ones. 

The most tragic and pathetic episode was the main piece of broast as I spotted some greenish color on the skin and inside on the meat.( Pics attached). Immediately I asked for the manager. On inquiring he told that it is undercooked' probably' and he will replace it and the plate was gone. I, however, suspected of "mustiness". At this juncture, I had lost my appetite and asked for the bill . The bill came and the broast didn't.  After the waiter was gone with the credit card , another came with the broast which was immensely overcooked. Didn't take a bite from it. As we were about to leave, a gentleman came with complimentary desserts . Those were also left untouched by us . To cut it short , if you are planning to visit Hot n Spicy in near future, please avoid ordering Afghani pulao at any cost and examine your food carefully as it might be stale and infested.  It used to be an amazing restaurant but regretfully this time they did not live upto the word. Pathetic food and extremely mismanaged.'

\xe2\x9c\x85Portland Winner

b"DUMPLINGS... = Pocket friendly Perfect Chinese Food ...
About last night, me and Miyan G,been to this small but delightful eatery in Gulistan-e-Johar near Kamran Chorangi, to satisfy our little cravings for Chinese Food.. and that too after reading very positive reviews on SWOT. We ordered Schezuan Chicken with fried rice, garlic prawns with egg noodles, spring rolls, wontons  and hot n sour soup in white.. 
The order came in time.. each and every item was perfectly cooked, hot and crispy and very very fresh.. one could feel the crunching veggies.. Above everything the servings were OMG.. like I could barely finish my meal and Miyan G was the same.. he even took away the left over and when I reheated later on, the noodle were still a quantity of full bowl.. 
Miyaan G tried some complimentary momos(dumplings) and that he didnt liked much.. not for his taste buds but they were also very fresh and the fillings too.. 
Their prices are veryyyy reasonable and the serving is quite beyond expectations(for those going crazy for ginsoy's 49% off and waiting for hours and hours for their orders and getting disappointed in the end by seeing the serving quantity)
It was an overall a very very nice experience as we have a habit of trying small eateries opened by young entrepreneurs.. atleast once a week and it did end well this time..! The restaurant manager Basit was courteous enough to accommodate us with our orders according to our demand.. and has some exceptional customer services skills.. 
Good luck Dumplings.. way to go! 
The best part..: they do not BEG to get reviews on SWOT after dinner.. IYKWIM \xf0\x9f\x98\x89"

b"People who are reluctant in paying delivery charges please start thinking 

Delivery charges goes to the one who delivers your parcel at your door step in your hand.

Ek insan jo pura din bike pe in any weather roams around, calls/texts you before coming, picks up the parcel from xyz place comes to you and deliver. 

Then comes to you no matter ap 1st ya 10th floor pe rehte hain, no matter apki lift nhi chal rhi hai, no matter uska bag kitna heavy hai and he can not keep that bag away halaat and chori k dar se.

And also, you're not the only customer he has to give parcel. These bikers at least deliver 10-12 parcels a day no matter whatever location. 

Ghar bethe aram se parcel apke hath mein mil rha hai and koi insan dhoop, thand,pollution, traffic se guzar ke addresses dhondh dhondh ke ghom keh apke hath mein parcel derha hai deserves 150-200rs. 

Petrol asman se nhi milrha unhe, apko bar bar call karke confirmation lene k liye unko bajiyan cards nhi dalwa ke deti, unke kahne ka time fixed nhi hota. Issi paisun mein se do have to utilise and then calculate kia they will be left with by the end of a day!?? 

Even food delivery guys!! They do midnight deliveries, early morning deliveries just to earn few extra bucks! 
Do no hesitate in giving some extra for the luxury that you're enjoying

Please don't treat labour class like slaves! It's one hardest job and least earned salary.

Please spread the message!\xf0\x9f\x92\x95"

b"Review: Chaaye Khana

I am sure you must have heard about Chaaye Khana opening in Karachi. If you haven't visited it yet, you should definitely give it a try!

So I will start with what I liked:

1. I LOVE the ambiance and decor! It's ahhmazing \xf0\x9f\x98\x8d (pictures attached)
2. For a tea and book lover like me, this is the perfect spot. There are comfy couches, dim lights, good music and and a chimney! Matlab pura mahol hai sukun se book parhne k lie (and of course to have tea!) 
3. Their serving sizes are really good! 
4. Their cigar lounge is a separate enclosure. So I don't have to even go through the 'smoking zone' to get to my nonsmoking area. (And I think the privacy is also good for those who want to smoke in peace)
5. Their fettuccine pasta had the perfect balance of cream and chicken, which is not the case at many other eateries. (I have tried almost har jagah ka pasta tou trust me on this \xf0\x9f\x99\x88)
6. I also liked their Moroccon chicken and Parmesan chicken in meals.
7. Their tea is amazing of course but couple it with the super moist French Toast or the Toasty Bites, for savoury lovers and voila! You have the perfect snack \xf0\x9f\x8e\x89
8. Their Strawberry Fizz is a must try too specially if you have a taste for khatti-meethi drinks.
9. AND not to forget the 15% discount on check-in and free tea on Tuesday for ladies \xf0\x9f\x99\x88

What I didn't enjoy so much:
1. I have been there 3 times so far and there is always some waiting time.
2. They don't give the option of French Fries as a side with many dishes \xf0\x9f\x98\x90

All in all, I have always had a good time at this new place in K-town."

b"14th Street Pizza.  Worst pizza in the history of bad pizzas.  I get that you have some kind of a promotion going on, but do give a disclaimer that quality is going to be horrendous.  

The dough was weird, double roti is a close substitute.  Sparse toppings, terrible pepperoni, bad sauce.  Just a bad pizza.  Nothing else.

If this is what fifth anniversary looks like, one shudders to think how the tenth would be like.  

It's not even cat food.  It's worse.

14th Street is going down the route of Pizza Hut.  Let's see who gets to rock bottom first."

b"Chupa Rustom.  It's a fresh bourgeoish take on the dying Irani cafe breed, with a well thought out iterative menu, and classic interiors.  

The interior has those rustic old city cafe notes, while the menu is a spin on the usual Desi offerings.  It's got a Desi tapas feel to it.  Order many small portions, and sample it all.  Hari bhari Mirchein, chapli Kebab, Darjan darjan Kebab, aaloo Kebab, and so on.  It's your usual fare with a twist, and a good twist at that.

Flavors were spot on, for whatever we sampled.  The Shahi Tukre being super -- with multiple layers of royalty.  One of the better Shahi Tukre commercially available.  

The pricing is competitive, with a more value driven approach calling for sampling and sharing a little bit of everything.  Per head cost would be in the range of PKR 700 to PKR 1200, depending on what is ordered. 

The service is a mess though, but it's got those 'teething' issues argument working for it currently.  If the management is able to streamline service, Rustom can be evolve into Sohrab.

Overall -- Chupa Rustom has a solid menu of small plates, and tries to capture that rustic old city feel.  The flavors are on point, while service remains the weakest link.  Rustom is gentrifying South Asian food, something close to home, and is often overlooked. 

P.S. Replace W-11 with X-10"

b'#TsgBloggerMehak

Eatery: Grotto Cafe

Verdict: Praise Cheesus for this Restaurant! From entrees to service, everything is impeccable.

Overall rating. 23/30 (Pretty darn Good!)

This was my 3rd visit to Grotto, for they are pretty consistent and deliver exactly what they show; unlike eateries that advertise one thing and serve a not so fancy KNOCK OFF.

Cheese is the cornerstone of every delicious food, but it's also good enough all on its own. Grotto introduced Raclette Cheese and I got all excited to try it asap. 

Grotto does amazing steaks which are flavourful, tender and juiciest even if the temperature ordered is well done. I thought of getting Raclette scraped over my favourite entree which was an additional PKR 550/- but I didn't.

What I Ate? Raclette Platter. Priced at PKR 2200/- this is the BEST THING EVER that serves 2 big eaters and 3 moderate eaters. The cheese was poured over the platter freaking TWICE. Platter included tender and oh so good, thin sliced beef steaks. It included another choice of beef which was more of a rolled up beef joint, stuffed with cheese. This was succulent and well seasoned but I clearly can't recall the name as of now. 

The platter also had a oh so yum side of potatoes, mushrooms and a lot of fresh lettuce, carrots, French beans and what not.

This all, not only added to the beauty, but also to the quality and quantity of serving. 

What I drank? Mixed Daiquiri. It was a fresh combination of berries and the best possible drink to wash it all down.  

The only downer was the pungent smell of the Raclette, which was strong and may irritate a few who have hyper anosmia. This was pretty tolerable and could be easily ignored for the Love of cheese. Adding to this, the manager told me about a vacuum machine they are installing in a day or two, to get rid of the smell. This may have been installed already, since I went some 4-5 days ago.

Conclusively, the line between "too much cheese" and "not enough cheese" is blurry at best, so no one's allowed to judge you.

b"Yesterday I, accompanied by a friend of mine, visited Shaikh's Dine In & Grill, at maskan chowrangi. Ordered chicken maskawa with side line mashed potatoes and rosemary chicken with sideline french fries. While we were fighting over what to order in appetizer, the waiter solved our dispute and advised to order Mandi. Obviously that's not a starter but he advised us to let go the idea of starter and try their newly launched mandi. I personally don't like this cuisine, to be honest. So I refused, upon which he told us it was  complementary for that particular day, as they wanted to get opinion from customers about their attempt to make Mandi. We consented for that and waited for our order. The Mandi was average, to be frank. Rice were of a mediocre taste but the chicken piece kept over it was succulent and palatable. Absolutely toothsome. We gave the honest opinion to them regarding it. When the main courses arrived, they too were savory and lusciously delectable as compared to what is being charged against them. Quantity, in fact, was also more than expectation. Had vouch 365 voucher so got a good deal of discount too. Even if there had been no discount, then also their prices are at the economical side. Good value for money. In the end, had two single scoops of ice cream on account of Facebook check in. Mango flavor was good, but the strawberry one was to die for. An amazingly pleasant and felicitous treat to my sweet tooth. Shall definitely be ordering again whenever I revisit them. Pictures attached for reference, total bill was pkr 900. The waiter, Mr. Sajid Ali, was a nice, friendly and decent guy who guided us through out. Over all a nice experience, shall be revisiting, specially during end of the month days when financial position is generally tight and the mood is to eat something congenial.
Rating;
Ambiance 9/10
Service 10/10
Food:
Taste 9/10
VFM 9.5/10
Overall experience 9/10"

b'#TSGBLOGGERHAMZA

Eatery: Ambrosia \xe2\x80\x93 Hi Tea (Ambrosia)

Verdict: Great ambiance, fast service but average food taste and quality.

Hi teas are on the up and coming these days around Karachi eateries, and every one of the fine dining restaurants is trying to bring the traditional "English style Hi Tea Experience" to you. With the likes of the Patio and the Deli, Ambrosia is also one of those that has brought in a similar style of Hi Tea experience. The menu, albeit, different than the rest but the overall experience was just average. 

Overall ratings: 

Taste/Quality: 6.5/10
Quantity: 7/10
Presentation: 8/10
Service: 7/10
Ambiance: 8/10
Location: 8/10
Per head: 895 + tax

The platter served, serves two people and the timings for Hi Tea are 4-7pm.

Savories: 

Turkey Sandwich \xe2\x80\x93 a multi-grain bread sandwich (single sandwich) cut in half with mayo, iceberg and a piece of frozen off the shelf thin turkey piece. Disappointing. 

Smoked Salmon Canape \xe2\x80\x93 a similar multi-grain bread piece sliced in half with, if you looked closely, you'll find a small piece of smoked salmon on top with a little spread of mayonnaise. Why even?

Tomato and Olive bruschetta \xe2\x80\x93 this was done like it was supposed to be done. Perfect. A nice piece of garlic bread, grilled, topped with salt and generous dressings of tomato and olives. But I had a hard time wrapping my head around why I should have this during tea time? Not something I believe would appeal to general public. 

Quiche Lorraine \xe2\x80\x93 the quiche lorraine was exactly what it was supposed to be. A small open crust pastry, savory, filled with egg, cheese and meat. This was rather nice, although inconsistency prevailed in most regarding the amount of egg present. Some of them had an overwhelming amount of egg which made it rather unpleasant to have. 

Chicken and Mushroom vol au vent \xe2\x80\x93 a nice one bite puff pastry topped with chicken pieces and mushrooms, dressed in mushroom sauce. A delicate and wonderful piece of hi tea savory. 

Mini Beef Burger \xe2\x80\x93 probably the best thing on the menu. Excellent patty, a soft bun and good enough to go along with the menu. 

Desserts: 

Dark Chocolate Tart \xe2\x80\x93 a very well done dark chocolate, made with consistency and a nice crust at the bottom. 

Berry Muffin \xe2\x80\x93 I didn't try this, so I'll leave this open for comments if you have tried it. 

Drinks: 

You get served with either tea/coffee/green tea and an Iced tea \xe2\x80\x93 all your choices. Very standard coffee, nothing too special. 

The presentation was up to the mark, the place was clean, hygienic. The servers there were polite and they had a relatively faster service than most. The restaurant in its own is pleasant place to be if you're going there for fine dining. Nicely lit, a very fancy d\xc3\xa9cor and great ambiance. Fall in love with the restaurant once you walk in.

Suggestions: May be change your menu a bit. If you're trying to bring in the English Hi Tea experience, might I suggest you try scones as well. Have a separate menu for each week and most importantly, focus on the taste of what you serve. The sandwiches and canape can be brought up a notch. 

P.S: I know some pictures might be blurry, I'm still learning - bear with me. Thanks.'

b"#TsgInternAlishba

London Fries 
Nearly bland, expensive food accompanied by poor service. This place is for people with extreme patience. 

Overall Rating: 4/10 

Stopped by LuckyOne Mall where I spotted this little eatery. The name somewhat appealed to me and I thought I'd give it a shot. Maybe not one of the best choices I ever made. 
Being a seafood lover their menu mainly comprised of different fish items with several components, I wanted to go something off of the average fish and chips and asked the counter service guy for the spiciest thing on their menu to which he recommended their Grilled fish fillet. 

Grilled fish fillet: according to them this was the spiciest thing they had on their menu that would suffice for 2 people, It was inclusive of 4 spicy fish fillets and 2 sauces (1 green chutney and the other ketchup) and 1 soft drink can 

Service: Service was incredibly slow we were asked to wait for 15 minutes even though there was no one else at the counter beside us. But since it was to be prepared 'freshly.' we couldn't question the time limit. After 15 minutes they said to wait for an additional 5-10 minutes as it wasn't ready yet. I was skeptical since fish does not take that long to fry whatsoever plus it wasn't a weekend and there was no rush at all. 

Presentation and Taste: Finally we got our order, that consisted of 4 tiny pieces of fish fillets that did look spicy and it was served with two sauces over the side and garnished with a few vegetables. 
We dived in and well unfortunately the 'spice' affect was limited to the coating of the fish, nonetheless it was pretty bland (which wasn't really expected) the fish pieces were very small and was downright tasteless. 

Price: A small platter of 4 fish fillets + 2 sauces garnished with salad and a can of Pepsi costed me around Rs. 580+ The least they could do is serve their fillets with fries. The quantity definitely wasn't enough for the price they were charging. 

Ambience: Since it was a mall and London fries did not have a reserved seating area the ambience was just okay and was kinda noisy. It would be better however If they had reserved their own seating area. 

Food: 4/10
Price: 4/10 
Ambience: 4/10
Service: 3/10 
Quantity: 3/10"

b"#TsgInternAlishba

Broadway Pizza

Good food for half the price, Poor service. When in doubt trust Broadway, always! 

Overall rating: 7/10

I was at LuckyOne Mall the other day, and after hours of walking/shopping (caution: if desi mom's say you're going shopping for only an hour, trust me you're not) I was starving and wanted to try something my taste buds were already aware of as I didn't wanna risk my hunger, so I thought what better of an option then pizza itself? Out of all the choices, I stopped at Broadway. 'Lucky' for me Broadway was selling their Large pizza for half the price! 
PIZZA for HALF the price? I couldn't resist.

WestSide Garlic (w/ stuffed crust + 2 extra sauces): Being an Italian cuisine lover- I opted for something creamy, so the person who took my order suggested I go for west side garlic, I trusted him and went for it. 

Service: Service was slow, considering it was rush hour they told us the order would take 15 minutes but we got it after like 25-30 minutes which is a shame to wait that long for a pizza over dine-in. 

Presentation and Taste: After the long wait I couldn't wait to dive in, the pizza was fresh out of the oven, looked great and it was piping hot. The stuffed crust was full of sauce and the crust was quite thin, light and airy just the way I liked. Toppings were sufficient enough and there was a lot of flavor, not to mention the  heavenly cheese strings in every bite! The suggestion was pretty good as the pizza was quite saucy and I loved the fact that you can actually feel the garlic and it's not just any other fancy name, the garlic and ranch sauce served with the pizza was a cherry on top- smooth consistency and great flavor. 

Price: The entire large pizza and additional sauces for the price of Rs. 650 instead of Rs. 1300 is definitely a keeper, Broadway surely has earned yet another customer in terms of taste- undoubtedly one of the best Pizza's in Town.  

Ambience: The seating area reserved for Broadway however was pretty small and the area was very crowded. 

Food: 7.5/10
Price: 10/10
Ambience: 3/10
Service: 4/10"

b"#TsgInternAlishba

ChachaJee
Medicore taste, Super expensive food, less quantity accompanied by average service. This place is NOT for people who are starving. 

Chana Chaat costed me (Rs.180) And a plastic cup of drink costed me (Rs.100)

Overall Rating: 3/10 

Stopped by LuckyOne Mall where I saw this eatery, I was craving desi food at that point, couldn't find a better option, thought I'd give it a shot, the name and the eatery looked fancy enough. Little did I know I'm not going to be receiving a meal worth the money I payed for. 
As the name suggests the entire menu consisted of desi food, from thalis to street food, everything was present. 
I didn't wanna go any different or take any chances, so I opted for the Chana chaat

Chana Chaat: Now this particular tiny plate consisted of 2 spoonfuls of Chanas, yoghurt, chopped onions and topped with chaat masala and papri, I also ordered a drink along with it surprisingly they had no cans or bottles available but instead they had their own plastic cups- which I would be completely fine with considering the fact that many fast food chains do the same. But it's the just the size and the price that got to me. 

Service: Well considering that it was street food, they had everything prepared over the counter and the guy just had to assemble a 'few' components and that was it. However we did tell him to prepare it while we wandered around in search of more food, when we came back they didn't prepare anything because 'they awaited our presence.' 

Presentation and Taste: finally it was time to dig in! I was really curious to taste that tiny little plate thought it might be full of flavor, sadly there wasn't much going on,    I couldn't Get the 'desi street food.' Feel, there weren't enough components and chutneys especially for the price they were charging! 

Price: The chaat costed me Rs. 180 along with a drink of Rs.100, total bill being 280. All I can say is the quantity definitely wasn't enough for the price they were charging. 
And Who even charges that much for a tiny glass of drink? 

Ambience: Since it was a mall and ChachaJee did not have a reserved seating area the ambience was just okay and was kinda noisy. It would be better however If they had reserved their own seating area. 

Food: 3/10
Price: 1/10 
Ambience: 4/10
Service: 3/10 
Quantity: 1/10

Note: the image below is not mine! However it is from chachajee and is quite similar to what I received."

b"#TsgInternAlishba 

Eatery: HEYDAY
Order: Banging brownie Rs. 250

Terrible ice-cream, poor service and pricey. Why is this place so over-hyped? 

Over all rating: 3/10

I was at lucky one Mall the other day where I was craving some ice cream, thought about trying 'HeyDay.' Since it's definitely the talk of the town for some odd reason. 
Went through their menu, looked absolutely scrumptious, the details, the ice creams and the sundaes. 

I went for the 'Banging Brownie.' Considering the reviews and well.. Who doesn't love Chocolate? 
 
Service: I placed my order and waited like 5 minutes for them to load my icecream which was fine till when the rest of my family had to wait for an additional 10-12 minutes while I had almost finished my icecream. Also note there was no rush at all. 

Presentation: I'll be honest, it looked absolutely amazing. The loaded icecream was every chocoholic's dream come true. 

Taste: After 2-3 bites, all I could taste was utter disappointment. The Ice cream legit had no flavor, the consistency was super watery and it felt like it had been made in water rather than milk, there was no 'cream' in that ice cream. 
No smooth and silky textures. Rather just plain chocolate ice cream full of ice crystals. Definitely the perfect example for 'Don't judge a book by its cover.' It had all the things in it to be a show stopper, but when it comes to taste honestly it felt like the local ice-creams you get that's usually sold over the streets. The toppings kept falling off, was way too messy. The worst part was that the brownie and nuts were all on top inside it was just plain chocolate ice cream. 

Price: The ice-cream costed me Rs. 250. If they're really charging that much for their 'ice-cream.' I honestly wouldn't want to pay a single penny for that, but with the over loaded toppings it was just below average. 

Service: 2/10
Price: 3/10
Presentation: 5/10
Taste: 2/10"

b"The True Betrayal:Ginsoy 49% Off 

I ordered from ginsoy today at 2:00pm. To start off the lady who picked the fone was extremely rude and manner less. She kept yelling over the fone and stopped listening mid way. Anyhow she told me that there is no commitment of time as to when food will be delivered to you and it can take upto 3 hours. I was okay with that since we were not that hungry that time.

When 2 hours went by i called them just to inquire the status of my order. I guess it was the same lady again and she again very rudely said we never did any commitment of time. I told her that i am just simply asking the status. So she said rider will come to you in some time. Like she was doing some ehsaan by sending order and i am some begger asking for food.

When the food arrived. I was so so disappointed with the quantity of the food. 

I ordered:
1-Dynamite prawns
2- Classic chicken chilli dry (single serving)
3- Chicken chilli (single serving)
4- Mix rice (family)

Firstly she sent 8pc +4pc prawns whereas i orderd 8pc only.

The most dissapointing thing was the quantity of the food. Normally a single serving is more than enough to fill up 2 people's stomachs. However, the classic chicken and cherry chill was in such less quantity that it was barely enough for one person. There were literally only a bunch of chicken pieces. Cherry chicken had the similar situation. 

Ginsoy should have mentioned that they will cut down the quantity of the food by 60% in discount deals so at least customers don't get manipulated by their so called discount. 

I am not gona lie, food taste was yummy as usual. Classic chicken chilli was great and so were prawns. 

I am gona attach the pictures of single serving that i ordered today Vs the single serving i ordered at their outlet when i visited them a week ago before any discounts and you can see it for yourself. 

My only complain is Ginsoy don't cheat your customers because someone like me who really love ginsoy and visit often feel so betrayed and it makes me question the ethics of the brand."

b"#TSGBLOGGERHAMZA

Eatery: The East End 

Verdict: Basic, homely, comfort food ingredients used to elevate a five-course meal with a fine dining experience. You won't get anything like this in Karachi, and that much I promise you. 

Overall Rating: 9/10 
Average hit: PKR 2500/- 

Located literally at the East End of the city, off Khalique uz Zaman road (Punjab chowrangi), nestled in a bushy corner \xe2\x80\x93 this place welcomes you with serious home feels. Coveted with a nice parking space right outside the place, upon stepping out of your car you'll notice a giant crow with a wooden background awaiting your welcome. 

It's a small, cozy place, with a very comfortable ambiance, well lit and a plush interior. The first look is welcoming, and you see waiters in crisp whites bringing you two menus \xe2\x80\x93 signatures and specials. 

The way it goes is something like this \xe2\x80\x93 in a five-course meal you only order your main course and you get 03 appetizers with it, 04 seasonal fruit drinks (shot glasses with slushy texture) and then at the end a dessert of your choice. You start off with a chilled detox water consisting of beetroot, lemon and mint and then your appetizers start coming in along with your drinks. 

The appetizers are crafted according to your entr\xc3\xa9e's styling. We were a bunch of 4 people so we ended up trying all their appetizers: chilies stuffed with mixed spicy pickle with flour based crackers to just soothe the spice, sweet boiled potato with crispy paapar and a chilly based dressing, boiled potato dressed in mint yogurt with fried egg plant and assortment of dressings, cannoli type sweet potatoes with herbs and tamarind sauce, three different types of bite sized parathas (sweet, savory and spicy), BBQ fried prawns, flour based twisted rolls stuffed with minced beef and tamarind sauce. 

Yes, I just finished the list of the appetizers. Each one of them had a superb unique taste and it would be unfair to differentiate them on basis of taste. Just to make things clear, one person gets three appetizers, so you might just get 03 of those appetizers depending on what you ordered. 

Finally, here's a list of my breakdown ratings: 

Taste: 9/10
Quality: 9/10
Quantity: 9.5/10
Presentation: 9/10
Ambiance: 8/10
Location: 7/10 (difficult to locate, unless you're using google maps) 
Value for money: 7.5/10

My main course was a classic Burn's Road Khatakat \xe2\x80\x93 served with garlic parathas. I am not much of a heavy eater and because of the whole list of appetizers being presented, I had to give up on my main course midway. Which made me realize that five course meals aren't my thing, lol. But the dish in itself was sublime. Perfectly spiced khatakat, well balanced flavors, less oil, generously served and just went very well with the whole meal. 

The drinks they served were an imli and gur slush, kiwi slush, mint lemonade slush, orange juice slush, and a pomegranate and black pepper slush \xe2\x80\x93 all shot sizes. 

At the end, you have a choice of gajar ka halwa, khajoor ka halwa, malpuris, and kulfi. For me the khajoor ka halwa was superb. I would get that on top of any other dessert, any given day. 

Long story short, this place is an experience of an own. If you have the budget, and someone you want to impress, then well \xe2\x80\x93 this place won't let you down. 

For more food goodies, follow me on: www.instagram.com/hamzasfoodventures"

b"If there's any place I can trust to serve quality food, with amazing service after Kolachi is this place called Meat The Cheese.

100% recommended. Would love to visit again and again."

b"Sooo i am one of those lucky persons who availed the 49% off on Ginsoy. We reached there at 8.30 so the representative told us to wait 40 minutes but she was kind enough that she called us in 10 minutes. The ambiance was little messy just because of the discount they're offering. 
So we ordered 4 items which were prawn balls, beef fried rice, beef mangolian and American chopseuy. 

The first thing we ate was the prawn balls and it was totally totallyyyyyy divine. I mean it was beyond perfect. I am a hugee fan of prawn and those prawn balls totally made my day 10/10 for prawn balls. Highly recommended 

The second thing was American chopseuy which was a total failure. I won't recommend it to anyone just because it has noooo taste. No chicken n beef element. I won't order it ever in my life tbh. 2/10 for chopseuy. (2 numbers for the egg at the top which was yummy) 

The third thing was Mangolian beef. I am utterly in love with this dish. My taste buds were shouting delicious. And it was totally complementing the beaf fried rice. A big thumbs up for mangolian beef 10/10

The fourth and the last thing is beef fried rice which were yummy. The aroma of the rice was like Wowww. And most importantly the quantity of the rice. I ordered single fried rice and 3 persons ate from it easily. 9/10

Tge the total damage was 1433. But when i read the general sales tax it was 13% like isn't it too much? They wrote that they're applying 7% but when the bill came 13% tax was applied on that. Its a big disappointing thing. It means they're offering a discount of 36% ? They should write this thing in the terms and conditions. 

Anyways if i ignore the bill stuff it was a fine experience."

b"In my experience there have been a very few restaurants that have nailed the art of a good eatery that being: quality food, great ambiance and good service. And Sultan comes on top of the list.
I have hosted two parties over there and everytime my experience has been exceptional. The very first time I planned to host a dinner there, I was very hesitant (it being a new eatery) and called them first. The person who spoke to me, Umer, was a gentleman and eased all my qualms. He guided my about the dishes and made sure my guests were attended well. The second time the service was equally good. The waiters were attentive and kept asking if everything was upto the standards.
The best thing I like about this place is the quality of food. The main highlights for us are: shahi mutton pulao, malai boti, palak paneer, achari handi and chicken tikka karhai. The food is really really good! And the ambience is perfect for formal gathering.
This time i cancelled an item from my order as the food was quite enough and i found out after coming home that they hadn't removed it from my bill. Although it was a genuine mistake from their part but the guy Umer apologised and was not only ready to refund the amount but he also offered to drop it off at my place.
All in all they truly know how to make a customer happy. I have become their loyal customer and I hope they maintain their standard in the long run.
P.S. Since I didn't get time to take pictures, I'm attaching the pictures from their page. The dishes were exactly the same as shown in pictures."

b'Tried a new plc called Goodfellas Pizzeria Khi last night and i must say that it was a great experience. Their food was excellent. We ordered peri bites and chicken strips as starters. I have tried peri bites at so many places but none of them were as good as original nandos ones however goodfellas has definitely outdone itself. Love how spicy and crispy they were. Chicken strips were equally delicious. 

Last but not the least we ordered their pepperoni pizza, cream tikka and tex mex pizza. They were pipping hot and delicious. Im a huge pizza fan and have tried many pizza eateries but @goodfellaspizzeria takes the cake.

The place had good ambiance as well with really good music and a newyork theme. My little nephew and niece both enjoyed lounging on their cosy bean bag chairs section.

Definetly plan to take my collegues and folks here for their pizzas next time.'

b'Hey Food Lovers,

After searching the Swot group for best fish grill in gulshan, Mamu Fish Grill came up the most :) 

So i went there to try it only to be impressed and highly satisfied with the taste and quality of the food :) Ordered a full heera fish ( red snapper ) which costs Rs.1200/kg and quarter kg prawns which costs Rs.800/quarterkg. Both the items were very fresh! 

To reach there just take a left from Dunkin Donuts on University Road and go straight. It will be on ur left side besides Donutz Gonutz along with Hot n Roll Snacks, it is a part of the Revive Snack Bar where you can have all sorts of desi snacks like paani puri and chaat as well as chinese. Has street sitting with tables and chairs. The family lounge isnt much but once the food arrives it doesnt even matter.'

b"Meat The Cheese.  The theatrics fade, and the food is underwhelming.  

The raclette cheese buzzfeed-ish theatrics were on point, but the food was just flat.  The service is good though, and people like the theatrics -- so why not.

The tenderloin steak was bad.  Served Medium, with a layer of cheese on top, it eventually morphed into Bihari Kebab.  The type of Bihari Kebab you make on third day of Eid, while you're an amateur -- and are then pushed away by family because you're screwing everything up. They may rename it to Bihari Steak.

The lasagna was devoid of any layers, with lots of qeema.  The burger was ordinary, much better options available elsewhere.  Massive portions don't always mean good flavors, and that was the case here.

Average cost is around PKR 1000 per head, and service is prompt.

Overall -- Meat the Cheese didn't live up to the expectations, or the hype.  It may be kosher for Instagram/Snapchat stories, but doesn't do much in terms of flavor.  Avoid the steak, unless you want a Bihari spin on it."

b"Meat the Cheese has the worst customer service ever!.. I went there last saturday with my husband and ordered their burger and a steak (btw, they just have one item each on their menu for steak and beef burger). They served the burger first and we had to wait for the steak to arrive. We waited 20 mins! Until that time my husband had stopped eating his burger and waited for my order to arrive. Obviously we wanted to eat together!  My husband had called the waiter numerous times to ask where the steak was! Finally when they were willing to answer our query, one of the servers came to our table to inform that they had 'forgotten' to prepare the order of steak ! .. and it will arrive soon. Obvioulsy, when the steak finally arrived the burger had gone cold, to which they said if we bring you a new one you'll have to wait again and the steak will go cold :/ .  thank fully they heated it up (atleast) and altho i had planned to ask for the cheese topping which they're so famous for, I was in such a bitter mood until then, that i totally didnt feel like it, at all! thanks Meat the Cheese for ruining our lunchdate :(   (which we rarely go out for, as we have three kids).  They served a complimentary desert in the end as apology, but the lunch was ruined. Dont think we'll go back there again."

b'Dinner at Flo. One of the few places you can visit on a whim without having to worry about the food. Solid no brainer.

Started with the portobello which was great as always. Baked delicately, served with rocket and balsamic. Mains included spaghetti with chili lime prawn and steak with morel mushroom sauce.

The spaghetti was balanced beautifully with tanginess from chunky tomatoes and acidity from the lime. The steak was done just right with a side of potato gratin and veg.

Dessert was tiramisu. Served at the right temperature with luscious mascarpone and a sprinkle of chocolate flakes.

Flo is simple and classic. It has held out the test of time and remains a constant favorite. A meal truly savored!'

b'-

Last Sunday I visited Bloomsbury Caf\xc3\xa9 solely and entirely based on the reviews that I read about its breakfast\xe2\x80\xa6 apparently it was one of the best Cafes for breakfast. Here's my experience.

Ambiance:  It is a fusion of modern caf\xc3\xa9 and classic design. What I really like about the interior that it is not showy and exudes elegance. It is a cozy place with comfortable seating (baring two that are placed with the pillars).
Staff is friendly and diligent. 

9/10 for the ambiance.
Food: I ordered "The English Platter" \xe2\x80\xa6 it offers two fried eggs, a bacon, sausages, CROISSANT, beans, butter, jelly, breads and a hash brown.  A pretty good deal for Rs.520 without tax. 

The fried eggs were nicely presented. However, the yolk was slightly overcooked and wasn't exactly runny. Croissant (my major reason for ordering this) was fresh and yummilicous. Hash browns also tasted good and so did the bacon. Sausages were okay, not that good but not bad either. 
I think if the yolk was not overcooked, I would have given it a good rating. But since it wasn't, I would only give it 6.5/10.

My friend tried Eggs Benedict Turkey and thought turkey was pretty salty but rest of it was good. It was for Rs. 570. 

Drinks: Since tea perks me up and I can't start a day without a cup of tea, I was slightly disappointed when I saw it on the menu that they only offer black tea or a shot of vanilla/choc etc in it. However, when I told the manager that I wanted to have a mix cup of tea (means with milk in it), he happily agreed and told me that it can be arranged. 

Tea was good and strong. It was for Rs. 140 without Tax, I think it is reasonable.

Total damage: Rs. 1492.

Verdict: Recently, I have tried a lot of new places but most of them turned out to be a damp squid, however, this one is added to the list of my "go-to" places because it is nice, cozy and offers reasonably good food. 

I would give it 8/10. 

#bloomsburycafe'

b"Thought to avail the discount at ginsoy...turned to the worst decision ever. Made the online order...after waiting for 10mins I called to the number provided..which was inactive so checked their FB page they have provided few other numbers...on calling them the representative told me it is smchs branch n north Nazimabad branch will deliver to Gulshan area. I called the North Branch n they said they will call to confirm within two minutes. After waiting for next 1 hour. I again call to the North Branch n they said they haven't received any order n smchs might have received it...however I had asked him that I had made the online order...I'm concerned who is going to deliver it n when...upon inquiring further he said madam I had told u we didn't receive ur order. I called back to the smchs guy n he said we received ur order...apne North Branch forward nhi kia...I was astonished that when there is no option provided online to opt the branch how can I forward it to any of ur branch..he said I'm forwarding it to the North Branch...within a min I got a call that madam we received ur order but u will get it after 2 hours ap btadein Kia krna hai! 
Means I ordered at 8 after wasting one hour struggling between their branches I need to wait for 2 more hours! The way he had called it was obvious they don't want to deliver. 

First of all when u don't want to deliver post it this offer is only for take away or dine in 
Secondly, when we are ordering online,customer has no idea which branch will cater it. So u need to be efficient n if u can't handle online orders then don't give this option
Thirdly, u r lossing ur customers due to bad customer representative service. As I'm a regular customer of ginsoy since days it was only at Shahbaz.
Ginsoy has gone awami!"

b"Karachi guy 
Finally I visited this place MEAT THE CHEESE since I was in a mood to have cheesy cheese and I have been seeing these posts on SWOT guide. Dekha tha ab try bhi kar Lia.
We ordered what seemed to be attractive and unique on the menu for appetizers we ordered , wicked mushrooms and artichokes.
Honestly I loved the wicked mushrooms and lasagna on a roll 
For the main course we ordered the steaks since I have heard alot about their steaks. Chicken bhi (the daily grill Rs765) try Kia beef bhi (tender loving loin Rs 1195). Regularly karachi Mein milnay walay steaks say buhut different tha and yes it was a surprise to my taste buds in a good way. Wohi Hur jaga milnay walay flavours say hat kar khaya kuch tu maza aya.
Sub say achi baat garam garam cheese mere khanay per pour ho rahi thi! And I was just loving it ! And lasagna on a roll which was also full of cheese :) 
Since we were beyond full after such a cheesy meal we didn't order any dessert! The meal was fulfilling and the service was excellent. The waiters were very polite and friendly.
Over all experience was good.
Next time will try their dessert too for sure as I was really tempted to do so magr jaga hi nahi bachi thi."

b'Had "Mandi & Madbee" today for the first time @Ibn-e-batuta. Base course was rice for both of them however to my ashtonishment following are my observations:

1. The rice served has a common household name that is "Tehri".

2. Chicken tikka is the same as it is always.

3. Salad also has a common household name called "Kachumber"

4. Finally the side line also had a "Timataar ki Chatni".
