b"With all the new pizza joints mushrooming up in K-Town, I ended up ordering from Eataly - Rich Italian Flavor, which boasts of offering authentic Italian pizzas (thin crust), for a lazy Saturday night in. 

I ordered their Mexican Chicken and Spicy BBQ chicken pizza. I had asked for the pizzas to be delivered at 8:30PM Sharp and to my delight they arrived on time which is a big BIG plus for any delivery joint! So for delivering it on time I give them a 10/10.

Both the pizzas were piping hot, the Mexican Pizza had a very distinct and unique flavour and lived up to the Mexican name as the hotness/spice factor was on point. Though they could've used a bit more cheese in this one so I would rate this a 7/10.

The bbq chicken pizza was a definite hit with the family! Ample chicken, ample cheese and enough mushrooms and olives as well as some sweet corn on top of this pizza added to its rich flavour..and of course the cheese sauce accompanying it complemented the flavour perfectly! (Going to be ordering this one on a regular basis) so it definitely deserves a 9/10.

The two pizzas (10 inches) came as part of a deal which was priced at PKR 999 which is a steal considering the price factor and the two pizzas were enough for 4 people. 

Accompanying the pizzas was also the Nutella Banofee Pie (complimentary) which proved to be the perfect end to this meal!"

b"#TSGBLOGGERANASKHAN
Venue : Chaupal Desi Exotic Buffet
Date : 31st May 2017

Eating out and raving about food has never been my forte. I'm that person who goes out not to enjoy scrumptious delicacies but to be immersed in the ecosystem of the restaurant and then eat whilst keeping a sharp eye on the service.

Now, a planned event with the fellow Swoggers led me to Chaupal. If I would be extremely honest, I did not carry any subliminal persuasions to go visit that place by any means and had obvious reasons for that.

Anyways, let's discuss Chaupal. I didn't know what that mean and googling it suggested that it's called ' Open Community Space'. I reached the venue just at Iftar time, gave the car on valet and hopped straight in towards the reception.

Now as they say, ' You never get the second chance, to make a great first impression ' and the lady at the reception nailed that immaculately. Let me elucidate how ?

Usually you go to a place, they ask for table / reservation et cetera. Though, that lady didn't do anything like that. What she did was more wonderful to me than anything else. Before even uttering a word, she offered me to sit down and brought a plate of 'Khajoors' to open the Iftar. Probably this act might sound a bit normal to you lot, but as I reiterate again, for me eating food is probably the last thing on the list at the Restaurant. I go out to meet new people, get acquainted with the decor and theme of the restaurant and to divulge into the logic of the designer, food artist, menu specialist, owner's perspective  and most importantly - to fathom upon the reason what made them people setup this restaurant on the first place, because it cannot be just commercialised stuff behind setting up a restaurant which can cater more than 200 people with plethora of food options from BBQ, CHINESE, SEA FOOD, THAI, ITALIAN, DELI ITEMS, IFTAR ESSENTIALS & OTHER SWEET / SAVOURY SNACKS.

Coming back to Khajoors now, I had a few of them, to get my ample share of ( Dietary Fiber, Vitamin B6 & Folate). Upon finally entering the main food court, I was greeted by my lovely fellow SWOGGERS i.e Maha Mamoon & Arham whilst the infamous Reza Merchant who never fails to keep check on me if I have arrived, truly love that gent much.

At that moment, most people were sat on their tables and enjoying their scrumptious food. It gave me an opportunity to have a stroll around the buffet area and see what the buzz is all about and I assure you, that I wasn't disappointed.

The food was sizzling from everywhere, the chefs were all wearing hats and aprons and hygiene was top notch. I noticed hand sanitisers available at every nook and cranny and different tongs were placed delicately beside every food item. It's extremely critical and was much pleasing for me to observe that, because I have severe Shellfish allergy, i.e an intolerance of Prawn, Fish or any seafood being on its own or mixed with any item even by a hint.

I admired the whole structure of Chaupal. The centre lobby has all traditional items from Biryani, Qorma, Karahi, Pulao, Sajji, Mutton Ghost, Palak Paneer, then it further extends to Italian wing with all the Pastas, Tarragon Chicken, Spaghetti Bolognese and then concluding it to the Sea Food enclosure containing Fried Fish, Prawns, oh there was ample Tartar sauce too there.

But after monitoring all those enclosures, I headed to my favourite and only point of interest; the BBQ AREA and in my sheer white plate, I poured Reshmi Kebabs, Malai Boti into it. You know when you pour Malai Boti from the spoon or spatula, it gets so sticky on it and you have to bang it on your plate to let go of those Botis, trust me I didn't have to do that. It poured nicely and gently and didn't resist at all, like the Malai Boti knew she was made for me and greeted me with her arms wide open. Okay melodramatic much, though pardon me if I get emosh much with BBQ (Proteins and Gains if you know..)

Now with my plate sorted, I headed on the upper wing to meet the rest of the SWOGGER TEAM, most didn't know me due to obvious reasons but still I sat with the lovely acquaintances and finally started my food. It had been only a minute or two passed and I see well dressed gentlemen coming to me and inquired about what drinks I would like, I requested only water and within a minute a bottle was presented to me.

The food tasted superb, all the BBQ items were marinated properly and were not rushed on the grill and as most Buffet restaurants do, loading up the containers to the brim, I didn't find that at Chaupal. The chefs there were strictly cooking and replenishing on ad hoc basis, which I found so attractive that everything you were being fed was so fresh and straight from the pan or grill, depends whatever you were eating. The photo attached can elaborate a bit of the peculiar interest I have in Food not.

Once done with the BBQ, I headed down to offer Salah and was pleased to observe a nice cosy Mosque on the corner with Wudu facilities as well, These things are worth mentioning because these MATTER to me a lot, because focusing on the human element of any business can never ever be detrimental and that's what Chaupal has offered me.

FOOD (8/10): Exemplary, everything was divine, nothing unprecedented happened. The whole experience was extremely polite, stress free and handled all with perfection by the Manager who was continuously monitoring everything.

QUALITY & TASTE (18/20): Exotic enough to evoke my memories of the amazing bbq I used to have with the lads back during summers at Hyde Park.

PRICE (10/10): At 999 Rs, nothing beats that. I could suggest everyone, specially families to go there. It's probably the finest not just in terms of the best bargain, but a wide array of food options catering needs of all, even children.

MENU SELECTION (8/10):  Pretty admirable, as stated above. You'd spend a good few minutes drooling across food being cooked, in my case Sajji was the personal best. Like you could see it roasted in front of you and the chef would dice it into pieces, top it up with lemon zest and hint of paprika. A must try item indeed.

LOCATION (5/5): Exceptional, located on Main Karsaz. Parking is a bit of choas, but where it isn't in Karachi? Got Valet available.

AMBIANCE / SERVICE / HYGIENE/ FOOD PRESENTATION ( 18/20)

It's an outdoor restaurant with the ground floor has roofing and fans options, the upper area doesn't have any Fans as of yet, which was bit of a lethargic dilemma, as Karachi's weather hasn't been very polite since some time now and humidity was killing. But still, It didn't stop the waiters and other house keeping staff to be in their top behaviour and served us in the finest way possible. 

Hygiene was strictly adhered to as well, with the used plates been taken by the staff promptly and also fresh cutlery was readily available.

Food presentation was immaculate too, I do not posses photos but they did carvings on several seasons fruits and the dessert section was also colourful enough 
to attract a large chunk of audience.

Total A: 47/50
Total B: 23/25

Overall score : 70/75

Suffice to say, Chaupal deserves an applause, not just by catering splendid food but also the level of top notch service standards set by them. It was one of the kind places, I left happily and kept contemplating about it on my drive back home. That is, the whole experience, the essence of our desi food and pride associated with it. I wish the management all the best for their future endeavours and keep up the immaculate job."

status_message:
b"The Valley - A review long overdue! 

Happened to try this fairly new eatery few weeks back but our experience wasn't as good as we thought it would be after entering the venue.

Ambiance first; simply loved being seated there! It's a homely and a very cosy place to dine out with an indoor and outdoor setting both. They do special arrangements for birthday parties, bridal showers etc and have a private area as well that you can book to have your own space totally. Their courtyard is pretty much fancied up, good newsss for all the people who love taking pictures! ;)  

Moving on to food, they have a pretty extensive menu which includes Pakistani cuisine as well. Impressive! We ordered Chicken and Mushroom Soup and Nachos as starters. The Valley Grilled Chicken, Tuscany Pasta, and Pepperoni Pizza as main courses.
 
Soup had profuse amount of chicken and mushroom; it was very close to the one available at Hobnob Express. Loved scraping the bread bowl. Price and quantity justified! 

Nachos were totally off, I have had much better nachos else where. 

We had Xander's and Bloomsbury's pizza in mind, were craving for something like that but this pizza left us utterly disappointed. Least liked dish of the day. It costed us Rs. 875+tax, tasted more like an ordinary bakery pizza and was even smaller than the standard regular size. 

Tuscany Pasta was better in all the main dishes we ordered. 

Their Grilled Chicken had nothing special in it, just the usual grilled fillets with a very mediocre tasting sauce. 

My friend wasn't a fan of their peach tea either!

b'Sometimes, some people here make me laugh - not at some good jokes, but their silly complaints and cries. The other day I saw a post about someone complaining about the price of a sandwich and even coming down to prices of individual food items. First and foremost, did you NOT know the price in the first place? If you did read so in the menu, in NO WAY is the restaurant to be blamed except for the quality and taste (which, is a genuine issue and to which this post is not related). Or did they suddenly come up and tell you something like "hello sir/ma'am, we just raised price of that very burger you ordered by 200%, 30 seconds ago, and you have to pay for it"?

Do you guys even realize the restaurant owners are not only supposed to make some profit (no they don't have families to support, of course) and pay wages, but they have invested huge amounts in the business for you to show up, get to occupy seats in their limited space, and enjoy the free air-conditioned and comfortable environment? Just now I saw another post complaining about the price of a mineral water bottle. For capitalism's sake! Are you guys even serious? That's how the world works! If you want the bottle for the same price, what's the difference between having invested in a small corner shop and a big restaurant? Why would they spend so much money and hire so many employees (thus make jobs for these same people who complaint unnecessarily)?

Talk some sense, will you? If you are really worried about the high prices, then well n good - save your hard earned money and also support the less financially stable by purchasing that mineral water or sandwich from your nearby shop/restaurant. You can simply not visit 'that expensive restaurant' in the first place if you genuinely believe they are looting you and that would be a sane decision to make.'

b"Living on the other side of the bridge, its quite seldom that you get to squander money over some fancy joint. So with all the savings, I finally decided to try the restaurant with the roots from Lahore... HOWDY'S at LuckyOne Mall..

Ambiance 8/10
The ambiance of the restaurant was amazing because of it's American wild west's theme with all those cowboy hats and fancily styled interior and outdoor seating. Despite all this, the restaurant was filled with smoke for some reason which forced us to leave the indoor and to sit outside... \xf0\x9f\x98\x94

Food 8/10
Coming to the food, the menu was fancily designed, or it was rather ciphered with complex styling. We were a group of 5, so we ordered 3 steaks and 2 burgers. I ordered a steak for myself; one thing I didn't read in menu was that the steaks were of chicken \xf0\x9f\x98\x90.... Def my mistake... But, surprisingly, the grilled chicken turned out to be great. It was the Desperado Steak. Properly grilled without being dry topped ( or what you wanna call it) with the jalapeno sauce and a side of mashed potatoes did make it a reasonable combo... I would have called it amazing but the price tag it had was a whopping 849 Rs ( or bucks as written on their menu... I'm glad i didn't have to pay that amount in dollars). Keeping money aside, it was amazing.. I also ordered a Yee Haa Mint Margarita which was decently priced at 189 Rs. 

Overall, it's a great variety added with all it's funky styling, but it seems to be overpriced compared to its competitors in town offering similar or better burgers and steaks at a much lower price."

b"I paid a visit to Moos and Clucks for lunch with a couple of my friends. Located at Gulshan (near Karachi University), it was good in terms of the ambiance and location. Furthermore, they plan on opening up another branch in the near future and also plan on providing deliveries, which will be a great addition. 

Moving on to the food, we started with an excellently prepared appetizer, Crispy Chicken Poppers. They were scrumptious. 

For the main dish, we opted for three different types of burgers; Jalapeno Royal, Mushroom Cheese and Portland Winner

Out of the three, Mushroom Cheese was the winner as it was absolutely mouthwatering. The patty was juicy and flavorsome while the sauce was just the right amount. As for the Jalapeno Royal, that too was delicious, and couldn't be flawed. However, the Portland Winner, I wouldn't say was a disappointment, however did have a few flaws. Firstly, the burger was way too saucy, and second, the patty wasn't as well done as compared to the other burgers we had tried. In my opinion, reducing the amount of sauce used would definitely compliment the burger much more. 

Overall, the experience was truly satisfying considering the reasonable prices in regard to the serving size and the luscious food. I would highly recommend this place to everyone and specially all the millennials out there."

b'I went to Icemokes DHA branch to try the liquid nitrogen icecream. Instead, I went with the recommendation of their waiter and tried this new dessert "Parfait". They serve two Parfaits chocolate and tropical. I wasn't in the mood for chocolate so I tried the tropical one. It was a combination of two scoops of ice creams and pineapple and Oreo and some other fruits. It was really delicious and worth the price. A really great combination. 
They claim that they are the only cafe who serves Parfait but it's hard to believe considering the face that there are so many dessert cafes in Karachi. 
It took a little time to prepare but the thing I really liked was that they used fresh fruits instead of canned fruits.
Will definitely try it again. Next time: Chocolate Parfait. 

Parfait: 9/10
Total damage: Rs 380/-'

b'Review - Royal Rich Bakery

Bought these cakes few days back from Royal Rich Bakery. Each year on my list January is the month which is full of birthdays. And what can be better when you can avail some good offers. I got Mud and Malteser Cakes, both were good and had a good amount of chocolate to satisfy your cravings for chocolate. Overall loved their packaging, it is done with black and gold to give a royal look. Box itself looks like a present! I availed my bogo.pk app voucher and of course got another cake absolutely free.

Mud Cake: It was a bit dry not that moist as it looked and as it should be but it tasted good. Cake design was nicely done, neat work! And it had balanced amount of sweetness. 

Malteser Cake: It was really rich and gooey, super moist too! But there were no Malteser inside the cake, only five used for decor! It would be really good if they would have added few crushed Malteser inside as well to give it a proper Malteser touch and taste.'

b"If you are a chaat/pani Puri person, then you shouldn't miss this place.
Went for dinner with my family to this newly opened salt and spice lounge named Chatoray at bahadurabad.
It is a small,brightly lit place , offering the great ambeince and comfort with food.
For appetisers , we went for peri bites and stuffed cheese balls, they were fresh and tasted delicious \xf0\x9f\x98\x8d
My mother orders khausa and she loved it.
They had paratha too so if we can't find pizza in the menu, we went for the pizza paratha \xf0\x9f\x98\x82
Ordered chatkhari katori chaat and their gol gappa shots , they were fresh and tasted divine. In burgers I went for the Mexican burger and boi it was spicy and delicious .
It had a beef steak piece, and like all the spices and sauces , big in size burger tasting great.
.

status_message:
b"Bon Bistro...wut??

Order:
.mushroom melt (beef)
.double melt (beef)
.cheese loader (chicken)

patty stuffed with cheese is an interesting concept. their burger sauce is good. their buns are plain but ok not everyone likes sesame seeds i guess. their patties are ok. BUT
they are overloading the flavor with cheese. i mean you can hardly taste their lovely burger sauce, you dont taste their jalapeno, you dont taste their patty. the cheese is like a Pakistani feudal lord who doesnt want his supremacy challenged by any other flavor. tomato was the only thing that stood out and not in a good way (1 thick chunk in the center? wut?)

cheese loader (chicken) was ok, i could taste the chicken as well as the burger sauce. the onion was neatly packed in a corner instead of being evenly distributed

the double melt (beef) was...uhhh i couldnt taste much of the burger melt thanks to lord cheese that coated my tongue with each bite making sure i taste nothing else

the mushroom melt (beef) oh i know you, my favorite burger from burger lab. youre gonna be amazing
lol nope. lord Cheezus has invited a friend here. brine. thats right. brine. aka salt water. the stuff mushrooms are dipped in for preservation. 1 bite and my dad's blood pressure shot up. Don Cheezo Corleone and his henchman, Brine the saltwater, made it a burger i'd certainly refuse

Bill: 750 (their prices are good though)"

b'DO DARYA is Karachi Food festival street 24/7 12months a year. 

one of the GEMS there have decided to have a family style festival in their premises for KARACHIites.

they very generously invited a few SWOGGERS to their opening night for a SWOT ANALYSIS

a well known SWOGGER Adil R Hussain who is a budding connoisseur of grilled meats and buffets lead the team of very had to please SWOGGERS - Hina Ilyas, Reza Merchant, Mehak Shoakat and Mian M. Ali Hassan.

they assessed the venue, the service the food and the event in the same discerning way that their keen eye has become trained over the last 18months of officially SWOTTING.

their individual reviews will appear as comments. but this is the aggregated result of their visit

COMBINED RATING - 53.3/75 (71.2%) 

EACH AND EVERYONE OF THEM COMPLIMENTED ON THE SERVICE AND FRIENDLINESS OF THE STAFF, 
THE LOVELY AMBIANCE
GOOD TASTING FRESH FOOD.

the few areas that were lacking was DESSERT - we all look forward to a refreshing dessert after a large buffet

the first day was NOT festive enough -  not enough lighting and the music was not fun.

BUT an overall a good fun way to spend with your family in one place.

#tsg #tsgblogger #swotanalysis #charcoalgrill #theswotsguide'

b"Hello swottiees,
As you all know that we have inaugurated a new cafe by the name of 'Once upon a time' which is adjacent to the old cineplex cinema. It is cafe offering the people of Karachi an opportunity to experience a distinctive taste of street food from around the world. 

Now for the first time in Pakistan, we have opened our basement for 'guests'. By guests, we mean the talented youth of this country which desperately needs an avenue to showcase their talents live in front of a decent crowd for which our basement will be available every weekend. 
I believe that our country has immense ability plus expertise in the fields of music, standup comedy, and karaoke open mic. This humungous amount of talent which has been unexplored if directed in the right way can outshine the name of our country. I also think that the reason why our country is lacking behind our neighbors in the aforementioned fields is the lack of availability of platforms which encourage them selflessly to refine their skills and by providing such, we at OUAT will try to do the minimum contribution we can do to our motherland as it will be open for all from this Independence day. So, all the talented juvenile out there can walk in and show what they got every weekend at our cafe. 
Anyone and everyone is welcome without any discrimination!.  
So please Come and support us.

Contact me for further details and slot bookings.
03222888088/03331207865 or just inbox us on our facebook page.

Friday: Comedy Nights
Saturday: Open Mic for Everyone
Sunday: Music Night

P.S Our basement is also available for private bookings like birthdays, seminars and any kind of celebration in accordance with our rules and regulations.

#OUATBasement"

b"REVIEW TIME:
it was my brother's birthday and we decided to have a family dinner at Shisi. We reserved our table and asked for some decoration as it was a mini surprise for him. Everything was very well managed. The food tasted amazing. For starters we had their famous dynamite prawns and drumsticks. Crackers were served complimentary. Me being a chinese lover loved the spicy combination in their signature Siracha chicken. Cherry chicken was on the sweeter side. The rice refills were free and they refilled without us asking them again and again. Overall experience from food, and ambiance to service was amazing!
Highly recommended 
Total damage: 4085"

b'Please feel free to disagree, but Kolachi is the BEST restaurant in Karachi hands down. The food is excellent, but this place has taken customer service to another level. We ordered the hot and sour soup and it wasnt warm enough, the waiter was soooo apologetic and replaced it immediately. One of the glass was smelling really bad so we asked them to change it. The food arrived hot and was delicious as always. The servers were on their toes, but looking around I realized it wasnt just for us,  they were treating EVERY customer in their like a celebrity.  One place in Ktown where you dont have to be famous to get attention. Anyway, when we asked for our bill we were given free ice cream because "Sir we are really sorry glass change kervana para aap ko".Whaaaaaaaaaat sirf aik glass hi tou tha.  Its honestly not about the free food, but how they want everyone to leave happy. This place deserves an award of some sort.'

status_message:
b"A branded disaster.
Bar BQ tonight Luckone Mall

Starting with the seating arrangement. You get a single table for 4 persons with very less space to keep the ordered food.

Order:
Chicken wings: cooked quickly so it wasn't cooked well. You have to use force to eat the meat. 6/10
Bihari kabab: perfectly cooked. Good taste. 9/10

Chicken white karahi: first of all the menu does not mention the weight. It costs 950rs but its 500gm i guess. Do mention the weight so people can order accordingly. Very taste less runny gravy.
Highly non recommended. Quantity and quality both are poor. Picture speaks for itself. 4/10

Chicken Afghani kebab: received under cooked. It was done on the out side but literally raw on the inside. Was replaced but still didn't enjoyed. 
Not recommended. 5/10

Service: asked for water bottle during ordering but was given with the order. A guy came with cold drinks in a tray and ask us to take it by ourselves from the tray. \xf0\x9f\x98\x92
Very limited menu available as of now.

Kindly improve your standards as per your parent outlet which is  considered best in karachi.

Bad experience. Will not recommended.
Overall 6/10"

b'Cheers,
This is my first post here, well tbh me and my friends are crazy foodies and always looking in search of great taste irrelevant of brands as we are almost done with these brands stuff, this weekend we came to knew about Pizza Romeesa (Kind of a unique name) on saturday i came across through their page on FB (Link attached) we ordered 3 pizza malai boti, bbq, fajita. I am sorry i wasnt able to click some snaps as we were damn hungry and when the pizza arrived we were like halla bolll, the pizza was fresh, dough perfectly prooved, topping was amazing and the taste was awesome. On sunday i had to go at my friends place so i thought of a take away from Pizza Romeesa and also i was curious to meet the owner and inquire about the story behind the name, luckily he was at the branch i first ordered my take away and then on my request the owner himself came to meet me after some greetings when i inquired abt the name he told me that Romeesa is his youngest daughter and he wanted to start this new venture on the name of his daughter (Betian Allah ki rehmat he said) This was the Gulshan branch opp Metro The dine inn facility is available but needs some development thou. I would reccomend to all the peeps out there (who are taste-concious NOT brand-concious) A MUST TRY !! Following is the link of their page the owner requsted me to like his page and also ask my friends to like it as well. xD

https://www.facebook.com/pizzaromeesa/'

status_message:
b"The Valley
The restaurant has a large number of cuisines on the menu.The restaurant is neat and clean with nice ambience. We ordered Nachos, Supreme Chicken Steak, Chicken Parmesan, Crunchy burger and Lasagna.
Their Nachos weren't up to the mark. Best dishes were Lasagna and Burger. They served rice instead of fries as a sideline and didn't even change it and argued.
They didn't even give 18% discount mentioned on their website.
Food: 8/10"

b'A couple of friends and I went to The Valley last night. Worst experience ever. After waiting for 10 minutes to get a table, the manager told us that we could sit inside the room which is at the back side and pretty aloof but since there was no other option we agreed. While we were walking to this "room", we saw empty tables on the porch and the waiter and manager said we could sit there if we wanted. So anyway, we sat on a table on the porch area and even before we could give our order, some other waiter or manager (not sure) came to us and said can you go and sit on another table which was in the middle of 2 groups of men so we didn\'t feel comfortable and told them we didn\'t want to go. He argued for a good 10 minutes telling us that a group of 10 people had reserved the porch and we had to leave that table. Anyway, we told them that we\'d order and move if and when the group of 10 people came since we knew that wasn\'t true. Finally got to ordering and ordered 2 appetizers. It took them more than 35 minutes to serve the appetizers. That\'s not even it, they served us appetizers with one plate and one tissue for a group of 4 people! At this point we called the manager and said we\'ve had enough. Their staff was not only unprofessional but really rude as well. We also ordered pizza and we were in shock when we saw a huge pizza dish with a tiny pizza on it (attaching pictures below). They gave us a complimentary brownie which was a sweet gesture on their part but it was dry with stale walnuts.Taste wise appetizers were fine .but whatsup with this crappy service? That is totally not acceptable! Plus we ordered pepperoni pizza with had sausages not pepperoni. I guess they need to learn the difference between that.'

b"Went to The Valley for lunch for a friend's birthday. I called them a day before to book a table and asked for some decorations like balloons or maybe a birthday banner. (I had read in a review that they do it complimentary) 
So when we got there they offered us their party room. There was no decoration rather they just threw two bunches of balloons on the floor. 
We ordered 6 dishes:
- Mozzarella sticks (2) which were appetisers but arrived after the main course.
- Parmesan chicken. 
- Fettuccine Alfredo pasta.
- Tarragon chicken.
- Peri peri pizza (peri peri? wasn't spicy at all and the crust was thick and dry). 

There was no proper service. The drinks arrived before the appetiser, next came in the main courses and the appetiser came right after. When I say the food was tasteless, I really do mean it. I've never had such an Alfredo pasta that doesn't even taste like one!? The mozzarella sticks were really flat and broke as we picked them up, they tasted pathetic without the sauce served with them. 
The pizza was again bland, why would they even name it Peri Peri!? All we could taste was the thick and dry crust because the topping literally had no taste. 

I complained to the person who came in to ask about the food. He offered to order something as a takeaway but how was that suppose to make up for the tasteless food? They didn't offer anything complimentary, not even their service! \xf0\x9f\xa4\x97

The total bill was around Rs. 6120, including tax and service charge. We were 7 altogether."

b"One has to wonder what Foodpanda Pk really charges for. Today I placed a delivery order from  Xanders Cafe. through Foodpanda. Whenever I order directly from xanders I have always had an amazing experience but unfortunately I made the mistake of ordering from foodpanda. I get a call from the Foodpanda rider that he has dropped the food and gone. I said, I didnt get it. He argued, I'vedropped it. Turns out because I had paid in advance and foodpanda had received the money he just dropped it at a random house and decided whats the issue, we have already got the money. Finally after numerous messages I got through to foodpanda and they said an hour after dropping the food at some random persons house they will pick it from them and give it back to me. I refused and said now I want a refund as I paid good money for food which could have been treated god knows how by someone random. They said ok we will have it done. 20 minutes very sneakily their rider picks up that same food and drops it at my house. Foodpanda is no longer responding have taken the money and dropped food which could very well have been tampered by someone. It is in an awful state. Came to me after lying outside at some random persons house for 2 hours. Absolute scams foodpanda are.\n\nP.s that's literally how I've received my 10 am breakfast (at almost 2). Restaurants should seriously consider breaking ties with Foodpanda since its coming down to credibility and the restaurants may lose potential customers."

b'Went to Xanders tipu Sultan road yesterday for anniversary lunch with kids and hubby. Loved it from the minute we stepped inside. The decor the ambience the service the food everything was up to the Mark! I had the tomato soup with roasted basil and corn. It was perfect texture and tasted super yummy. We ordered the margerita pizza for starters which again was super yummy. Thin crust perfectly cheesy. For mains I had the grilled red snapper with sweet potato mash. Perfectly juicy tender tangy and the right amount of spicy. Hubby had penang chicken curry with white rice. Super delicious. Perfect texture and taste. Tender chunks of chicken. Kids had fried chicken burger and the Alfredo pasta with Turkey bacon. Both loved their food and gobbled it down. Dessert was Blondie something with caramel sauce and vanilla ice cream. Divine!! Servers were courteous and quick considering it was packed. Had a great experience. Fantastic anniversary lunch. Thank you Xanders. Did not take the food pics as we were starving.'

b"DESI GUY 
Review for Dialogue

If we start from the ambiance, then the restaurant takes 8 out of 10, nice interior and sitting arrangement.
As I was bit hungry that time, though I was more interested in their food, and I ordered; 

1- Classic Nachos 
Salsa sauce was like tomato puree, sour cream was bitter we all four didn't like that and we put that aside. Overall nachos were average in taste.
rate: 6/10

2-  House Ground Beef Burger
It was just the very normal dry beef burger, petty was too dry, over all no sauce was complimenting the burger's entire taste. I will not mention other brands but many other small burger joints have great taste as compared to this cafe's burger.
rate: 3/10

3- The Club Sandwich
Club sandwich was just ok, I was expecting something different with the taste but it was like Aone's type. So it killed our expectations, we can have two clubs from Aone like these in the same price of which Dialogue is offering.
rate: 4/10

4- Oven Roasted Chicken
Same here, this entry also killed our expectations, we expected boneless piece with proper seasoning of rosemary and Parmesan. But both's elements were missing in the taste and it was very normal roasted leg piece without any marination. 
rate: 2/10

5- New Zealand Rib Eye Steak 
I am steak lover, and tried almost every where in Pakistan, I also make steaks at home. When I was ordering the from the steaks section, I asked the waiter which steak is the best in your menu he suggested the most expensive one amoung the others which cost 1400/100grams. I asked the weigh per serving he told 180 to 200grm per serving and I confirmed him the order with mentioning that to keep proper eye on temperature, I ordered medium well. 
Disaster happened when I saw steak in my plate, it was well done of well done, overcooked piece of beef, you can see blackening of both sides in the picture. The cut was not even ribeye, and overall it was too hard. I didn't even touched that steak and returned to them and never asked for new as it was too bad to ruin my mood and my appetite. 
rate: 0/10

Overall ratings: 3.8/10
Highly not recommended from my side to anyone.
Over all damage for four items 3,610, steak was cancelled.
PS: We went to the other place to complete our appetite.
Visit day: Sunday 5th Feb 2018
Time: Around 9pm"

b'So my family decided to go to Golden Bowl for dinner on my brothers suggestion since he went there last week and he had a great experience 
But guess what! 
It was not our lucky day \xf0\x9f\x98\x92
Anyways to start it up, we called them to reserve a table for 6 at 9 pm and we were there by 8:55 and yes we got our table immediately, from the interior it seemed like they got inspired from chop chop wok so the theme and the decor was more as less the same as Chop chop wok's , they have this wide window display like where you can see live cooking and the chefs doing their tricks while making dishes etc ( this was quite appealing to see)
Khair we ordered their all you can eat deal for rs 500 and we ordered 5 of these deals and soup for my mum and our server told us that food will take 35 - 40 minutes , we were fine with the serving time since that was acceptable and hence we started waiting, it was about 9:30 when this random customer started shouting at one of the managers that it has been half an hour and no one came to ask him for his order or anything and he was furious Khair they turned up the volume of the songs so that other customers couldn't notice about this guy bashing the manager but yeah we could hear all of it , it was like 9:50 when I inquired about my order to which the waiter said " 5 more minutes "  I was like okay at around 10:05 my dad lost his cool and then suddenly the waiter came with one dish ...
Yes! Just one dish , it was beautifully done and looked appealing too , since we all were quite hungry we attacked the plate and it got done within  few minutes, then after another 10 minutes when my dad scolded the guy about bad service and management , he brought the second dish and the rice was pretty cold as if it just came out of the fridge ... if Gordon Ramsey was there he would have sealed the place ! 
It was at this moment that we all lost our cool ( Im not the kind of guy who gets effed up so easily ) but yes I was furious so I just went to wash my hands and told the waiter " yaar aplog khaana toh layengay nahi toh bill hi ladain " to which the waiter took another 15 minutes to generate the BILL and he did that when I threatened him to leave the premises in a minute if he doesn't brings the bill... it seemed  like they were weren't even interested in collecting the bill. Just during the payment of bill this other customer also lost his temper and things were getting out of control for them, Khair we stood up and went to Desi gali toh eat some bunkababs and boy ! boy ! they were Goood! And then some chai and Nutella paratha to end the day on a good note but yeah golden bowl if you can't handle it, it's better to shut it down for once and for all ! 
It's just simply not your thing ! 
Best regards,
One furious customer \xf0\x9f\xa4\xac'

b"Review for Golden Bowl: 
If I could give this place zero I would. We arrived at 8:45 place was not full. Tiny space maybe seating 25-30 guests. Food came an hour late at 9:45 they had misplaced the order. 3 other customers had the same issue regarding food. 
One table told them to cancel the order and left after waiting an hour. They had come before us! 
One table waited 20mins for a cake slice. Table behind us were served uncooked noodles. 
The waiters were running around 'look busy do nothing'. No waiter would listen. When he did come around he said food takes 15-20mins and it had been 30mins already. When the food came it was average similar to chop chop wok. Had I known I would have gone there. We were not compensated in any way. No apology nothing. The manager wouldn't even come out of the kitchen to talk to the customers. We could see him in the kitchen since there were glass windows to show the food NOT BEING COOKED. 

Being a new restaurant I felt there service and management should have been more on point."

b"Karachi is all about food. Went to Chaayekhaana today. Because of long weekend it was very crowded with a 15 to 20 mins wait. The manager seemed very busy, I feel he could have handled better by making the conversations short with people around him.
I had baby G with me who was getting cranky cuz of lunch time. I would have appreciated if there was a kids menu / packed juices or anything that i could get for him while we were waiting to be seated.  
We were given seats in the lounge that they opened due to peak hours (traffic) 
I felt it was a little stuffy (room temp). The order was placed quickly but it took them a little while to get us our food. 
I dont blame the rush as staff should be prepared. 
I had to ask 3 to 4 times for napkins and water. 
Food tasted great, but Service is the main ingredient. 
Seating space: 6/10
Food : 7/10
Service: 6/10
My experience: 5.5/10
Advice: If you know you're busy and dont have enough room or there is a long wait please keep some snacks /packed juices or any sort of refreshment for little kids, pregnant women or anyone who asks for it."

b"Finally ate THE QUADRA, a presentation by Burger Lab. I mean what were you guys having? This burger was downright delicious! I mean for me it was what a beef burger should be like. Fully loaded and juiciest to the last bite! I mean it is plentiful. Two people had one burger in lunch; it was enough. If you don't have a gigantic appetite than a single Quadra burger is enough for 2 persons. I have always been a fan of their burgers and this one definitly tops the list. 

I don't know if there is consistency issues but the outlet at LuckyOne Mall did full justice to this mighty meat delight. The beef patties, 4 slices of cheese, sauces and mayo, onion rings & pepperoni! Everything was there in one burger and its definitly a juicy , chessy, messy meaty treat!

Value for money 9/10
Size 8/10(for the monstrous appetite)"

b"Whoever wrote the review with all the praises about Chatoray, You sir are a either a liar or you need to get your tastebuds checked.

After reading that review, we decided to give it a try and ditch our regular Mirchili. We ordered one Khaousay, one Chicken Cheese Paratha and one plate Gol Gappay. We instructed the waiter to get it made as spicy as possible. 

The Khaousay was nothing less than a bad daliya with noodles, tasteless and flavourless. 
Ate half a bowl of it just for the respect of food.

The chicken cheese paratha had literally no cheese in it. Again it had no flavor or spices. The only thing spicy and tasty enough was the green chatni provided with it.

Gol Gappay were made fresh and looked promising with the glass shots. But as we took the first bite of it and drank the sauce. It felt like 'Saunf ka paani'. We asked the waiter to make the sauce more spicy, so he went and brought the same sauce in a bowl.

So we left them and head to pay the bill. Upon telling the cashier about our experience, he was courteous enough to let go the price of Gol Gappay and said that he will forward our complaint about chicken cheese to the manager.

Also he gave us the 20% check-in discount they are offering even though we didn't check in.

But as he gave me the bill, it had the Gol Gappay mentioned and charged again. Upon scrutiny, he said it was a mistake. Rectified it and paid the amount that was around 470.
But they still gave me the bill generated earlier with the full amount. (Good luck explaining that to FBR) even though you are not registered yet. 

Overall, I would say that they still need improvements in their recipes and even in training their staff.

Food 3/10
Ambience 7/10
Presentation 5/10
Overall 4/10

Final verdict, won't be going there again."
